Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.65,0:00:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,(弗吉尼亚州匡蒂科附近森林)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.21,0:01:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,朱迪·福斯特(克拉丽丝·斯塔琳)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.68,0:01:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,安东尼·霍普金斯(莱克特·汉尼拔)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.68,0:01:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,斯科特·格林(杰克·克劳弗尔)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.68,0:01:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,泰德·拉文(詹姆·甘姆-野牛比尔)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.68,0:01:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,安东尼·希尔德(基顿医生)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.19,0:00:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,(CRICKETS CHIRPING)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.61,0:01:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,(BIRDS CALLING)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.37,0:01:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fn黑体\c&HFFFFFF&}沉默的羔羊{\fn\c}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.65,0:01:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,(PANTING)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.48,0:03:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,MAN: Starling!\N斯达琳！
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.15,0:03:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Starling!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.36,0:03:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Crawford wants to see you in his office.\N克劳福德要见你
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.41,0:03:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir.\N谢谢
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.53,0:03:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,(伤害)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.73,0:03:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,(苦难)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.94,0:03:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,(痛苦)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.14,0:03:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,(喜欢它)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.83,0:04:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- Clarice.\N- Hey.\N- 克拉丽丝\N- 你好
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.71,0:04:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,(PEOPLE CHATTERING)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.71,0:04:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,(行为科学组)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.01,0:04:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,...so there shouldn't be any problem if you could...\N……应该不会有任何问题，只要你能……
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.18,0:04:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- You looking for Crawford?\N- Yes, sir.\N找克劳福德吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.72,0:04:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He should be back in a couple minutes.\N他应该很快就回来了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.93,0:05:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you wait in his office?\N在他的办公室等一会吧
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.10,0:05:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N好的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.39,0:05:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think they were over in flushing...\N再说我觉得他们太过于……
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.78,0:05:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,(比尔剥下第五个人的皮)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.07,0:05:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Starling,\N斯达琳
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.24,0:06:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Clarice M. Good morning.\N早安，克拉丽丝
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.45,0:06:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Mr. Crawford.\N早安，克劳福德先生
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.87,0:06:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to pull you off of the course at such short notice.\N抱歉突然把你召离课堂
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.25,0:06:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Your instructors tell me you're doing well.\N你的导师说你很不错
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.29,0:06:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Top quarter of your ciass.\N是班里的高材生
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.75,0:06:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope so. They haven't posted any grades yet.\N希望是吧，他们还没有公布成绩
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.09,0:06:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A job's come up, and I thought about you.\N有一个任务要办，于是我想起你
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.76,0:06:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a job, really.\N这不是正式的任务
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.97,0:06:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,More of an interesting errand.\N更像一份有趣的差事
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.72,0:06:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit down.\N坐下
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.39,0:06:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.\N是，长官
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.26,0:06:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember you from my seminar at UVA.\N我记得你上过我在弗吉尼亚大学的研讨班
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.77,0:06:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You grilled me pretty hard, as I recall,\N我记得，你追问我很紧……
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.73,0:06:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,on the Bureau's civil rights record in the Hoover years.\N问我本局在胡佛年代的公民权利记录
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.27,0:06:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave you an "A."\N我给了你“甲等”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.69,0:06:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A-minus, sir.\N是甲下
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.61,0:06:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see. Double major, psych and criminology. Graduated magna.\N双主修，心理学及犯罪学，以优异成绩毕业
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.12,0:06:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Summer internships at the Reitzinger CIinic.\N在瑞辛格疗养院做过夏季实习
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.91,0:06:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It says here when you graduate,\N它说你毕业后……
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.87,0:06:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to come to work for me in Behavioral SClence.\N想在行为科学组替我工作
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.96,0:06:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, very much, sir. Very much.\N是的，我很想
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.54,0:06:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We're interviewing all the serial killers now in custody...\N我们正在访问被囚禁的连环杀手……
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.34,0:06:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for a psycho-behavioral profile.\N进行变态行为的分析
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.51,0:07:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be a real help in unsolved cases.\N对一些悬案会有很大帮助
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.30,0:07:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of them have been happy to talk to us.\N他们大都乐意跟我们谈
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.26,0:07:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you spook easily, Starling?\N你会否很容易受惊？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.68,0:07:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet, sir.\N不会
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.52,0:07:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the one we want most, refuses to cooperate.\N我们最想见的那个人拒绝合作
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.31,0:07:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to go after him again today in the asylum.\N我想你去精神病院找他
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.19,0:07:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And who's the subject?\N那个人是谁？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.90,0:07:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The psychiatrist Hannibal Lecter.\N心理医生汉尼拔·莱克特
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.49,0:07:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hannibal the Cannibal.\N食人狂魔汉尼拔
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.82,0:07:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't expect him to talk to you,\N我想他不会跟你交谈
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.83,0:07:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but I have to be able to say we tried.\N但无论怎么样我们都得尝试
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.66,0:07:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So if he won't cooperate,\N如果他不合作……
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.08,0:07:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I want just straight reporting.\N我希望你如实报告
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.66,0:07:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How's he look? How's his cell look?\N他的容貌和监狱里的状况怎么样？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.75,0:07:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he sketching, drawing?\N他有没有素描、绘画？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.46,0:07:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If he is, what's he sketching?\N如果有，他都画些什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.01,0:07:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a dossier on Lecter.\N这是莱克特的档案……
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.01,0:07:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A copy of our questionnaire and a special ID for you.\N问卷副本和你的特别身份证
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.64,0:07:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Have your memo on my desk by 0800 Wednesday.\N周三早上八点把你的报告交给我
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.44,0:07:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N好的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.06,0:07:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, sir, but why the urgency?\N对不起，长官，为什么这样急？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.32,0:07:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Lecter's been in prison for so many years now.\N莱克特已经坐牢很多年了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.32,0:08:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there some connection between him and Buffalo Bill maybe?\N他和水牛比尔是否有关联？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.57,0:08:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish there were.\N但愿有
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.53,0:08:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I want your full attention, Starling.\N我要你非常留意，斯达琳
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.41,0:08:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.\N是的，长官
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.54,0:08:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Be very careful with Hannibal Lecter.\N要非常小心应付汉尼拔·莱克特
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.58,0:08:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Chilton at the asylum will go over...\N精神病院的奇尔顿医生会……
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.50,0:08:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,all the physical procedures used with him.\N给你讲解接见程序
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.38,0:08:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not deviate from them for any reason whatsoever,\N无论如何不能偏离程序……
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.05,0:08:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're to tell him nothing personal, Starling.\N你绝对不能向他透露私人事情，斯达琳
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.72,0:08:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Believe me, you don't want Hannibal Lecter inside your head.\N相信我，你不会希望汉尼拔·莱克特知道你在想什么
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.39,0:08:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Just do your job, but never forget what he is.\N执行你的任务，但千万别忘记他是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.22,0:08:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is that?\N是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.18,0:08:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,CHILTON: Oh, he's a monster.\N哦，他是个魔头
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.39,0:08:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A pure psychopath.\N一个变态狂人
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.56,0:08:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So rare to capture one alive.\N可以生擒一个已很难得了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.86,0:08:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,From a research point of view,\N从研究角度来说……
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.23,0:08:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Lecter is our most prized asset.\N莱克特是我们最有价值的资产
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.24,0:08:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well.\N那好
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.24,0:08:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we get a lot of detectives here,\N你知道，我们这儿以前来过很多探员
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.08,0:08:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but I must say, I can't ever remember one as attractive.\N但我得说，不记得有过这么有魅力的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.41,0:08:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you be in Baltimore overnight?\N你会在巴尔的摩过夜吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.42,0:09:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this can be quite a fun town if you have the right guide.\N因为如果你有适当的向导，这可以是个很好玩的城市
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.59,0:09:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm sure this is a great town, Dr. Chilton,\N我肯定这是个了不起的城市
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.22,0:09:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but, uh, my instructions are to talk to Dr. Lecter...\N但给我的指示是要同莱克特医生交谈……
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.51,0:09:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and report back this afternoon.\N然后下午回去报告
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.43,0:09:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.\N我明白了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.60,0:09:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's make this quick, then.\N那么我们快点吧
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.10,0:09:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We've tried to study him, of course,\N当然，我们尝试过研究他……
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.85,0:09:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but he's much too sophisticated for the standard tests.\N但他太高深了，一般的测试都不适用
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.81,0:09:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my, does he hate us!\N哦，天啊，他多么讨厌我们啊！
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.28,0:09:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks I'm his nemesis.\N他觉得我是他的报应
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.82,0:09:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Crawford's very clever, isn't he? Using you.\N克劳福德真是聪明，对吧？利用你
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.82,0:09:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARICE: What do you mean, sir?\N你什么意思，先生？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.28,0:09:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,A pretty young woman to turn him on.\N找个漂亮的女郎来引诱他
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.62,0:09:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe Lecter's even seen a woman in eight years.\N我相信这八年来莱克特都没见过女人
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.41,0:09:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And, oh, are you ever his taste.\N而你正合他的胃口
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.96,0:09:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So to speak.\N恕我直言
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.46,0:09:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I graduated from UVA, Doctor.\N我毕业于弗吉尼亚大学，医生
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.30,0:09:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not a charm school.\N它不是一间仪态学校
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.63,0:09:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Then you should be able to remember the rules.\N很好，你该能记着那些规矩了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.92,0:09:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,(MAN SHOUTING)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.80,0:09:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not touch the glass.\N不要触摸那块玻璃
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.05,0:09:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not approach the glass.\N也不要接近那块玻璃
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.18,0:09:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You pass him nothing but soft paper.\N只可传递柔软的纸张给他
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.93,0:09:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No pencils or pens.\N不能传铅笔或钢笔
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.64,0:09:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No staples or paper clips on his paper.\N纸张上不能有钉书钉或夹子
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.81,0:09:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Use the sliding food carrier. No exceptions.\N只可用那个活动食物架传送，不得有例外
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.27,0:10:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If he attempts to pass you anything, do not accept it.\N如果他想给你传东西，不得接受
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.48,0:10:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand me?\N明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.61,0:10:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I understand, sir.\N是的，明白，先生
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.98,0:10:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,(BUZZER BUZZING)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.65,0:10:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to show you why we insist on such precautions.\N我让你看看，为什么我们坚持如此戒备
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.99,0:10:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,On the afternoon of July 8, 1981,\N在1981年7月8日的下午……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.70,0:10:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,he complained of chest pains...\N他说胸口痛……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.99,0:10:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and was taken to the dispensary.\N被带往医疗室
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.70,0:10:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,His mouthpiece and restraints were removed for an EKG.\N为方便做心电图，他的口罩被除下
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.50,0:10:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,When the nurse leaned over him, he did this to her.\N当护士靠近他身边时，他对她做了这个
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.17,0:10:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctors managed to reset her jaw, more or less,\N医生们多少算是重整了她的下颚……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.42,0:10:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,save one of her eyes.\N救回她一只眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.01,0:10:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,His pulse never got above 85,\N即使在他吃她的舌头时……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.76,0:10:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,even when he ate her tongue.\N他的脉搏从没超过85
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.51,0:10:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I keep him in here.\N我把他关在这里
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.64,0:10:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Chilton.\N奇尔顿医生
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.73,0:10:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If Lecter feels that you're his enemy,\N如果莱克特觉得你是他的敌人……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.90,0:10:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,then, uh, well, maybe we'll have more luck...\N那么，嗯，如果我单独去的话……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.36,0:10:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,if I go in by myself.\N我们运气可能会好一点
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.82,0:10:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?\N你认为怎么样？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.53,0:10:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,(BEEPING)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.20,0:10:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You might have suggested this in my office...\N你如果在我办公室时提出来……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.37,0:10:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and saved me the time.\N就可以省掉我的时间了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.29,0:10:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir, but then I... I would have missed...\N是的，但我……我会错过了……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.54,0:10:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the pleasure of your company, sir.\N与你同行的乐趣
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.54,0:11:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When she's finished, bring her out.\N她完事后带她出去吧
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.37,0:11:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. I'm Barney.\N你好，我是巴尼
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.37,0:11:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He told you, don't get near the glass?\N他告诉过你，不要靠近那块玻璃吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.37,0:11:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he did. Clarice Starling.\N对，他说过了，我是克拉丽丝·斯达琳
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.21,0:11:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm-hmm. Nice to meet you, Clarice.\N嗯。幸会，克拉丽丝
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.54,0:11:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hang your coat up here if you like.\N你可以把大衣挂在那里
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.09,0:11:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. I will.\N好的，谢谢你
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.63,0:11:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He's past the others. The last cell.\N他在最尽头的那个牢房
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.26,0:11:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep to the right.\N靠右走吧
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.51,0:11:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I put out a chair for you.\N我给你放了一张椅子
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.35,0:11:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes. That's very good. Thank you.\N哦，好的，太好了，谢谢你
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.81,0:12:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be watching. You'll do fine.\N我会看着，你不会有事的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.61,0:12:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,INMATE: Hi.\N嗨
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.93,0:12:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I can smell your cunt.\N我可以闻到你的私处
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.48,0:12:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.\N早安
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.15,0:12:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Lecter, my name is Clarice Starling.\N莱克特医生，我叫克拉丽丝·斯达琳
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.36,0:12:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,May I speak with you?\N可以和你谈谈吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.32,0:12:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're one of Jack Crawford's, aren't you?\N你是杰克·克劳福德的人，是吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.08,0:12:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I am, yes, sir.\N是的，我是，先生
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.45,0:13:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,May I see your credentials?\N我可以看看你的证件吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.00,0:13:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly.\N当然可以
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.34,0:13:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Closer, please.\N靠近一点，劳烦你
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.76,0:13:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Closer.\N近一点
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.24,0:13:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That expires in one week.\N一周内后就到期了
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.40,0:13:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not real FBI, are you?\N你不是真正的联邦调查局探员，是吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.24,0:13:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still in training at the Academy.\N我还在学院里受训
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.95,0:13:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack Crawford sent a trainee to me?\N克劳福德派个见习生来见我？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.16,0:13:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm a student.\N是的，我是个学生
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.12,0:13:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm here to learn from you.\N我是来向你学习的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.25,0:13:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you can decide for yourself...\N也许你可以自己决定……
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.67,0:13:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,whether or not I'm qualified enough to do that.\N我是不是够资格这样做
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.88,0:13:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm.\N嗯
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.88,0:13:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That is rather slippery of you, Agent Starling.\N你这人非常狡猾呢，斯达琳探员
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.60,0:14:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit, please.\N请坐吧
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.69,0:14:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then. Tell me,\N那么，现在告诉我……
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.53,0:14:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,what did Miggs say to you?\N米格斯对你说了什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.86,0:14:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Multiple Miggs in the next cell.\N隔壁的『多面人米格斯』
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.66,0:14:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He hissed at you.\N他向你发出嘶嘶声
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.32,0:14:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he say?\N他说了些什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.20,0:14:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "I can smell your cunt."\N他说『我可以闻到你的私处』
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.41,0:14:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.\N是吧
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.08,0:14:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself cannot.\N我可闻不到
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.38,0:14:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,(INHALING)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.09,0:14:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You use Evyan skin cream.\N你用爱肤恩润肤膏
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.31,0:14:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes you wear L'Air du Temps,\N有时你会用点L'Air du Temps香水……
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.60,0:14:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but not today.\N但今天没有
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.40,0:14:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you do all these drawings, Doctor?\N这些画是你画的吗，医生？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.44,0:14:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!\N啊！
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.28,0:15:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the Duomo, seen from the Belvedere.\N那是从观景楼远望的佛罗伦萨大教堂
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.03,0:15:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You know Florence?\N你知道佛罗伦斯吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.66,0:15:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All that detail just from memory, sir?\N那些细节都是来自记忆的吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.95,0:15:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Memory, Agent Starling, is what I have instead of a view.\N斯达琳探员，我只有记忆，没有景观
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.96,0:15:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\N那么……
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.17,0:15:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps you'd care to lend us your view on this questionnaire, sir.\N或许你可以在这份问卷上给我们一些见解，先生
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.09,0:15:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no, no.\N哦，不，不，不，不
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.80,0:15:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You were doing fine.\N你做得很不错
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.64,0:15:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You had been courteous and receptive to courtesy.\N你很有礼，而且能接受礼貌
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.85,0:15:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You had established trust with the embarrassing truth about Miggs.\N你很坦率告诉我米格斯的下流话，来取得我的信任
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.52,0:15:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And now this ham-handed segue into your questionnaire.\N现在却又拿出了这份拙劣的问卷
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.77,0:15:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,(CLICKING TONGUE)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.36,0:15:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't do.\N这可不行
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.11,0:15:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm only asking you to look at this, Doctor.\N我只是要求你看看它，医生
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.15,0:15:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Either you will or you won't.\N做不做随便你
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.32,0:15:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N对
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.03,0:15:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack Crawford must be very busy indeed,\N克劳福德一定是忙得不可开交……
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.20,0:15:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,if he is recruiting help from the student body.\N否则他不会从学校找个女学生来帮忙
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.12,0:15:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Busy hunting that new one, Buffalo Bill.\N忙于追捕那个新人，水牛比尔吧
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.00,0:15:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What a naughty boy he is.\N他可真是个淘气的坏孩子
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.50,0:15:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why he's called Buffalo Bill?\N你可知道为什么他被称为水牛比尔？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.13,0:16:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell me. The newspapers won't say.\N请告诉我。报纸上可不会说
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.59,0:16:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it started as a bad joke in Kansas City Homicide.\N是来自堪萨斯城凶案组的一个笑话
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.30,0:16:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They said, "This one likes to skin his humps."\N他们说，『这个人喜欢剥他猎物的皮』
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.64,0:16:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you think he removes their skins,\N你认为他为什么要剥她们的皮……
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.65,0:16:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Agent Starling?\N斯达琳探员？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.19,0:16:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Enthrall me with your acumen.\N用你的敏锐来振奋我一下吧
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.19,0:16:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It excites him.\N这样做令他兴奋
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.03,0:16:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Most serial killers keep some sort of trophies from their victims.\N大部分的连环杀手都会保存受害人身上的东西作为纪念品
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.86,0:16:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't.\N我可没有
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.24,0:16:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\N对
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.45,0:16:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you ate yours.\N你吃了他们
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.71,0:16:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You send that through now.\N把那个传过来吧
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.02,0:16:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\N嗯
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.73,0:17:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Agent Starling,\N哦，斯达琳探员
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.86,0:17:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you think you can dissect me with this blunt, little tool?\N你觉得凭这份拙劣的东西就可以分析我？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.91,0:17:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,No!\N不是！
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.37,0:17:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I... I thought that your knowledge...\N我……我相信你的学识……
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.99,0:17:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so ambitious, aren't you?\N你很有野心，是不是？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.62,0:17:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what you look like to me...\N你知道你拿着那个高级皮包……
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.95,0:17:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with your good bag and your cheap shoes?\N和穿着廉价鞋子对我来说像个什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.46,0:17:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like a rube.\N像个土包子
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.58,0:17:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A well-scrubbed, hustling rube with a little taste.\N一个干净、忙碌，带点品味的土包子
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.51,0:17:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Good nutrition has given you some length of bone,\N足够的营养给了你体骼的成长……
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.97,0:17:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're not more than one generation from poor white trash,\N但也只是从你这代起才跳出了白人下层阶层……
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.39,0:17:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,are you, Agent Starling?\N是不是，斯达琳探员？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.39,0:17:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And that accent you've tried so desperately to shed,\N你极力想摆脱那不由自主流露出的口音……
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.27,0:17:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,pure West Virginia.\N地道的西弗吉尼亚腔调
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.60,0:17:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,(IN SOUTHERN ACCENT) What does your father do?\N你父亲是做什么的？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.77,0:17:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he a coal miner?\N他是个矿工吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.94,0:17:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he stink of the lamp?\N他不是满身带着矿灯的臭气？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.02,0:17:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And, oh, how quickly the boys found you.\N还有，哦，那些男孩多迅速就搭上了你
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.73,0:17:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All those tedious, sticky fumblings in the back seats of cars,\N在单调沉闷、闷热肮脏的汽车后座里胡乱摸你……
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.36,0:17:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,while you could only dream of getting out, getting anywhere,\N而你却梦想着走出去，去任何地方……
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.20,0:17:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,getting all the way to the FBI.\N一直走到联邦调查局
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.21,0:17:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You see a lot, Doctor.\N你很有观察力，医生
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.04,0:18:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But are you strong enough to point...\N但你是否强大到能……
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.59,0:18:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that high-powered perception at yourself?\N用这敏锐的观察力来分析你自己？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.22,0:18:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What about it? Why don't you...\N怎么样？为什么你……
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.59,0:18:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you look at yourself and write down what you see?\N为什么你不探究一下自己，把观察所得写下来？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.10,0:18:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you're afraid to.\N或者你害怕这样做吧
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.40,0:18:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,(THUDDING)
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.48,0:18:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A census-taker once tried to test me.\N曾经有一个人口调查员想测试我
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.57,0:18:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I ate his liver with some fava beans,\N我把他的肝配着蚕豆吃了……
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.07,0:18:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and a nice Chianti.\N还有上好的基安蒂干红呢
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.33,0:18:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,(HISSING)
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.04,0:18:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You fly back to school now, little Starling.\N小斯达琳，你飞回学校去吧
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.50,0:18:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Fly, fly, fly.\N飞吧，飞吧，飞吧
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.52,0:18:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,(MIGGS MOANING)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.06,0:19:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,MIGGS: I bit my wrist so I could die.\N我咬我的手腕，那样我就可以死了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.53,0:19:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the blood!\N看这些血！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.70,0:19:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotcha!\N你上当了！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.45,0:19:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Miggs! You stupid fuck!\N米格斯！你这愚蠢的混蛋！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.37,0:19:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hannibal the Cannibal!\N食人狂魔汉尼拔！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.04,0:19:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Agent Starling! Come back!\N斯达琳探员！回来！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.71,0:19:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Agent Starling! Agent Starling!\N斯达琳探员！斯达琳探员！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.21,0:19:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I would not have had that happen to you.\N我不会让那种事情再发生在你身上的
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.67,0:19:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Discourtesy is unspeakably ugly to me.\N不礼貌的对我来说就是难言的丑陋
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.54,0:19:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then do this test for me.\N那么帮我做这个测验吧
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.88,0:19:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but I will make you happy.\N不做，但我会令你开心的
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.21,0:19:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you a chance for what you love most.\N我会给你一个你最喜欢的大好机会
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.13,0:19:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is that, Doctor?\N是什么，医生？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.22,0:19:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Advancement, of course. Now listen carefully.\N当然是升职。现在仔细听着
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.34,0:19:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Look deep within yourself, Clarice Starling.\N你自我反省一下，克拉丽丝·斯达琳
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.89,0:19:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Go seek out Miss Mofet, an old patient of mine.\N去找出莫菲特小姐，我从前的一个病人
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.97,0:19:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- M-o-f-e-t. Go now.\N- Doctor.\N- M-O-F-E-T。现在去吧\N- 医生
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.39,0:19:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think Miggs could manage again quite so soon,\N我相信米格斯不会这么快发作的……
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.39,0:19:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,even though he is crazy.\N虽然他是疯的
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.69,0:19:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Go now!\N快去！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.06,0:19:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,(INMATES SCREAMING)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.26,0:20:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,(BIRDS CHIRPING)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.81,0:20:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Bill.\N你好，比尔
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.65,0:20:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.\N嘿
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.82,0:20:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy!\N爸爸！
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.95,0:20:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Clarice.\N嘿，克拉丽丝
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.49,0:20:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?\N你好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.78,0:20:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get any bad guys today, Daddy?\N爸爸，你有没有抓到坏人？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.87,0:20:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No, angel, they all got away.\N没有，小天使，他们跑掉了
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.79,0:20:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw, shoot.\N啊，真糟
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.63,0:20:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,(DOG BARKING)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.30,0:20:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,(CLARICE SOBBING)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.35,0:21:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,FBI! Hands up! Don't move!\N联邦调查局，举手，别动！
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.81,0:21:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn around!\N转过身来！
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.02,0:21:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hands behind your back! Thumbs up.\N把双手放在后面！好的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.90,0:21:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,(SIREN WAILING)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.15,0:21:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're dead, Starling.\N斯达琳，你已经死了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.70,0:21:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Johnson, good job. Good entry. Good commands.\N约翰逊，进入和指挥都做得很好
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.58,0:21:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- Starling, where's your danger area?\N- In the corner, sir.\N- 斯达琳，你哪里有危险？\N- 在角落
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.70,0:21:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- Did you check the corner?\N- No, sir.\N- 你有没有检查过它？\N- 没有，长官
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.16,0:21:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the reason you're dead.\N所以你已经死了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.66,0:21:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,3-1-0-9?\N是3109？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.75,0:21:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Breaking doors or windows to enter or exit.\N打破门或窗闯入或者撤退
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.09,0:21:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Rule 404...\N404号规则呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.59,0:21:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,(巴尔的摩心理医生，获得最高荣誉)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.86,0:21:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,(著名心理医生被控谋杀)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.02,0:21:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,(PHONE RINGING)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.34,0:21:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,(食人狂魔审讯带来新的恐怖)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.36,0:21:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Clarice, phone.\N克拉丽丝，你的电话
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.82,0:21:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's the guru.\N- Crawford?\N- 是教官\N- 克劳福德？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.32,0:21:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Thanks, Ardelia.\N是的，谢谢，阿德利亚
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.95,0:21:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Starling?\N斯达琳？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.03,0:21:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARICE: Sir?\N长官？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.57,0:22:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Miggs is dead.\N米格斯死了
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.16,0:22:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Dead? How?\N死了？怎么会？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.75,0:22:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The orderly heard Lecter whispering to him all afternoon,\N守卫听到汉尼拔·莱克特整个下午对他低声说话……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.21,0:22:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and Miggs crying.\N而米格斯在大叫
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.33,0:22:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They found him at bed check.\N他们在夜间巡查时发现了他
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.54,0:22:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd swallowed his own tongue.\N他吞掉了自己的舌头
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.88,0:22:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Starling?\N斯达琳？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.55,0:22:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm... I'm still here, sir.\N是的，我……我还在听，长官
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.59,0:22:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I just... I don't know how to feel about this.\N我只是……我不知道对这件事该有什么感想
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.06,0:22:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to feel any way about it.\N你没必要感想什么
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.89,0:22:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Lecter did it to amuse himself.\N莱克特这样做只是为了自娱
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.81,0:22:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I know it got ugly today,\N我明白今天很难受……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.31,0:22:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but you mentioned a name at the end. Mofet.\N但你最后提到了一个莫菲特的名字
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.73,0:22:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Any follow-up on her?\N有后续行动吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.57,0:22:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, well, Lecter altered or destroyed...\N莱克特在被捕前……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.03,0:22:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,most of his patients' histories prior to capture,\N把大部分病人的病历销毁了……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.86,0:22:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,so there's no record of anyone named Mofet.\N所以没有任何名叫莫菲特的人的记录
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.74,0:22:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But, uh, I thought the "yourself" reference...\N但……嗯……我觉得他用了『你自己』这个词……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.08,0:22:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,was, uh, too hokey for Lecter,\N这对莱克特来说太做作了……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.95,0:22:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so I figured, he's from Baltimore,\N所以我想，他来自巴尔的摩……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.58,0:22:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I looked in the phone book,\N于是就翻查电话簿……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.08,0:22:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's a "Your Self Storage" facility,\N那里有一间叫『你自己』的自助式仓库……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.67,0:22:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,right outside of downtown Baltimore, sir.\N就在巴尔的摩市外围，长官
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.26,0:23:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Unit 31 was leased for 10 years,\N31号仓已经租了十年……
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.26,0:23:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,prepaid in full.\N租金是全数预缴的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.06,0:23:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The contract\N合约……
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.39,0:23:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the name of a Miss Hester Mofet.\N是签在海斯特·莫菲特小姐的名下的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.27,0:23:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So nobody's been in here since 1980?\N自从1980年就没有人来过了？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.07,0:23:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to my knowledge.\N据我所知是没有
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.53,0:23:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Privacy is a great concern to my customers.\N我的顾客都很重视隐私权的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.32,0:23:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,(GRUNTING) Yes, I won't disturb anything. I promise.\N好的，我保证不会扰乱任何东西
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.24,0:23:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be out of here before you know it.\N我很快就会离开
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.87,0:23:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- May I help you?\N- Yes, actually, you can.\N- 我能帮忙吗？\N- 是的，你可以
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.08,0:23:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,(DOOR BANGING)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.46,0:23:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stuck.\N它被卡着了
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.80,0:23:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We could return tomorrow with my son.\N我们可以等于明天跟我的儿子一起来
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.80,0:23:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What about him?\N他怎么样？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.63,0:23:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I would ask my driver to help you,\N我本可叫我的司机帮你……
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.97,0:23:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but he detests physical labor.\N但他讨厌体力劳动
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.31,0:23:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Great.\N太好了
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.06,0:23:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You just stay here. I'll be back in one minute.\N你别走开，我很快回来
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.79,0:24:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,(METALLIC CLANKING)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.55,0:24:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,(GRUNTING)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.30,0:24:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stuck.\N它被卡着了
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.68,0:24:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hand me that flashlight, sir.\N先生，请把那支电筒递给我
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.35,0:24:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,(METALLIC CLATTERING)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.48,0:24:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\N哦
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.90,0:24:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...\N嗯……
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.36,0:24:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If this door should fall down...\N如果这道门跌下来……
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.86,0:24:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,(CHUCKLES) or anything else, uh,\N或者有什么意外，呃……
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.24,0:24:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the number for our Baltimore field office.\N这是我们巴尔的摩地方办公室的电话号码
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.20,0:24:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, they know that you're with me.\N他们知道你跟我在一起的
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.08,0:24:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You call them if anything should happen.\N如果有意外你就给他们打电话吧
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.21,0:24:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Miss Starling.\N好的，斯达琳小姐
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.46,0:25:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,(TROUSER FABRIC RIPPING)
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.24,0:25:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,(RAIN PATTERING)
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.23,0:26:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,(THUNDER CRACKING)
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.74,0:26:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,(THUDDING)
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.94,0:27:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Clarice. Here. They're waiting for you. Watch your step.\N克拉丽丝，这边。他们在等你，小心你的脚下
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.57,0:27:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N谢谢
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.41,0:27:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARICE: Hester Mofet.\N『海斯特·莫菲特』
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.12,0:27:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an anagram, isn't it, Doctor?\N是拼字猜谜，对吧，医生？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.66,0:27:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hester Mofet, "The rest of me."\N意思是『我其余的东西』
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.04,0:27:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,"Miss The Rest Of Me," meaning that you rented that garage?\N『我其余的东西』，那表示车库是你租的？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.83,0:28:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N谢谢
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.71,0:28:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Your bleeding has stopped.\N你的血已经止住了
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.84,0:28:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you...\N你怎么……？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.05,0:28:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing.\N没什么的
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.88,0:28:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a scratch.\N只是擦伤而已
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.88,0:28:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Lecter, whose head is in that bottle?\N莱克特医生，那瓶里的头颅是谁的？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.35,0:28:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you ask me about Buffalo Bill?\N你为什么不问我关于水牛比尔的事？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.68,0:28:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, do you know something about him?\N你知道他的什么事吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.68,0:28:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I might, if I saw the case file.\N有可能，如果我看过他的档案
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.89,0:28:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You could get that for me.\N你可以替我拿他的档案
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.90,0:28:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we talk about Miss Mofet?\N我们为什么不谈谈莫菲特小姐呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.61,0:28:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanted me to find him.\N你要我去找他
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.98,0:28:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,His real name is Benjamin Raspail.\N他的真名是本杰明·拉斯佩尔
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.74,0:28:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,A former patient of mine,\N我的一个前病患……
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.57,0:28:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,whose romantic attachments ran to, shall we say, the exotic.\N他的恋爱对象，有点怪异
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.70,0:29:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not kill him, I assure you.\N我没有杀他，我向你保证
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.29,0:29:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Merely tucked him away very much as I found him,\N只是把他藏起来，就像我发现他时的样子……
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.08,0:29:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,after he'd missed three appointments.\N在他错过了三次预约之后
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.79,0:29:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you didn't kill him, then who did, sir?\N如果你没有杀他，那么是谁杀的，先生？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.17,0:29:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Who can say?\N谁知道呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.55,0:29:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Best thing for him, really.\N这对他来说是最好的结果了
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.30,0:29:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,His therapy was going nowhere.\N他的治疗完全没有效果
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.26,0:29:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,His dress, uh, makeup...\N他的裙子、化妆……
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.77,0:29:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Raspail was a transvestite?\N拉斯佩尔是个异性装扮癖好者？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.60,0:29:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In life? Oh, no.\N生活中？哦，不是
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.06,0:29:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Garden variety manic-depressive.\N不是，只是普通的躁狂抑郁
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.48,0:29:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Tedious. Very tedious.\N乏味，非常乏味
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.11,0:29:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just think of him as a kind of experiment,\N现在我把他看成是一个实验……
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.74,0:29:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a fledgling killer's first effort at transformation.\N一个初出茅庐的杀手的第一次转变的努力
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.32,0:29:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you feel when you saw him, Clarice?\N你看到他时有什么感觉？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.66,0:29:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Scared at first, then,\N最初吓坏了，后来……
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.58,0:29:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,exhilarated.\N就很振奋
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.54,0:29:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jack Crawford is helping your career, isn't he?\N克劳福德在提携你的职业生涯，是吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.96,0:29:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, he likes you, and you like him, too.\N看来你们互相倾慕呢
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.42,0:29:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought about it.\N我从没有想过
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.59,0:29:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think Jack Crawford wants you sexually?\N你认为克劳福德对你有性方面的欲望吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.67,0:29:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,True, he is much older,\N真的，他年纪大了很多……
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.26,0:29:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but do you think he visualizes scenarios, exchanges,\N但你觉得他对你有过想入非非吗？交换……
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.97,0:30:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,fucking you?\N操你？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.14,0:30:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't interest me, Doctor.\N这吸引不了我，医生
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.69,0:30:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, it's... It's the sort of thing that Miggs would say.\N坦白说，这是……这是米格斯会说的那种话
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.19,0:30:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Not anymore.\N他不会再说了
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.37,0:30:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Barney.\N谢谢你，巴尼
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.37,0:30:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,(INDISTINCT)
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.96,0:30:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARICE: What happened to your drawings?\N你的那些画呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.58,0:30:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Punishment, you see, for Miggs.\N惩罚，你知道的，为了米格斯那件事
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.30,0:30:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like that gospel program.\N就像那个福音传播节目……
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.26,0:30:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When you leave, they'll turn the volume way up.\N你离开后他们就会调高声音
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.38,0:30:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Chilton does enjoy his petty torments.\N奇尔顿医生喜欢这些折磨伎俩
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.26,0:30:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you mean by transformation, Doctor?\N你说转变是什么意思？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.73,0:30:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been in this room for eight years now, Clarice.\N克拉丽丝，我在这里已经八年了
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.44,0:30:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I know they will never, ever let me out while I'm alive.\N我知道在我有生之年，他们都不会释放我
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.70,0:31:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What I want is a view.\N我想要的是一个景观
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.03,0:31:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I want a window where I can see a tree, or even water.\N我想要一个能看到树和水的窗户
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.04,0:31:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be in a federal institution far away from Dr. Chilton.\N我想去一间远离奇尔顿医生的联邦监狱
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.58,0:31:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you mean by fledgling killer?\N你说『初出茅庐的杀手』是什么意思？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.42,0:31:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that he's killed again?\N你是否说他已经再次杀人？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.59,0:31:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm offering you a psychological profile on Buffalo Bill,\N我根据案件的证据，给你对水牛比尔……
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.93,0:31:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the case evidence.\N进行心理分析
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.43,0:31:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help you catch him, Clarice.\N我会帮你抓住他，克拉丽丝
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.61,0:31:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You know who he is, don't you?\N你知道他是谁，是不是？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.61,0:31:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me who decapitated your patient, Doctor.\N告诉我，谁把你的病人斩首了，医生
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.45,0:31:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All good things to those who wait.\N愿意等待的人才有好结果
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.74,0:31:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I've waited, Clarice,\N我已经等了……
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.08,0:31:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but how long can you and old Jackie boy wait?\N但你和老杰克能等多久？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.37,0:31:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Our little Billy must already be searching...\N我们的小比尔一定正在找寻着……
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.46,0:31:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,for that next special lady.\N下一位特别的女士了
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.05,0:31:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,∮ After all it was a great big world ∮
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.32,0:32:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,(田纳西州孟斐斯市)
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.34,0:32:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,∮ With lots of places to run to ∮
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.14,0:32:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,(SINGING) ∮ Yeah, and if she had to die ∮
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.97,0:32:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,∮ Trying she ∮
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.97,0:32:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,∮ Had one little promise she was gonna keep ∮
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.52,0:32:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,∮ Oh, yes ∮
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.69,0:32:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,∮ All right ∮
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.48,0:32:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,∮ Take it easy, baby ∮
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.49,0:32:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,∮ Make it last all night ∮
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.99,0:32:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,∮ She was an American girl ∮
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.13,0:32:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,(BEEPING)
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.02,0:32:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,(CAT MEOWING)
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.82,0:32:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, little cheeper.\N小猫咪
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.24,0:33:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be right there.\N我就快上来了
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.75,0:33:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,MAN: Oh, shoot.\N哦，糟糕
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.96,0:33:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Goddamn it.\N该死
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.35,0:33:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect! Jesus.\N太好了！天啊！
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.73,0:33:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I help you with that?\N要我帮忙吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.40,0:33:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you?\N可以吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.61,0:33:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.\N当然可以
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.65,0:33:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- Thank you.\N- That's all right.\N- 谢谢你\N- 不用客气
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.40,0:33:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You look kind of handicapped.\N你好像是伤残人士
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.66,0:33:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N是的
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.12,0:33:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it this far.\N我搬了很远了
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.28,0:33:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't get it up in the truck.\N但我就是搬不上货车
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.20,0:33:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Here. Just grab this.\N来吧，抓着，上！
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.25,0:33:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N好的
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.37,0:33:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Just set it down. That's good.\N好，把它放下吧，很好
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.83,0:33:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, get in the truck.\N你上车
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.17,0:33:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to push it all the way up.\N我想把它推进去
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.25,0:34:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I really appreciate this. Thank you. All right.\N真的很谢谢你
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.34,0:34:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N好的
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.42,0:34:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N谢谢
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.59,0:34:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Just go all the way back.\N进到后面去
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.34,0:34:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Is this good?\N好了，行了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.26,0:34:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's good.\N行了，很好
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.64,0:34:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great.\N真好
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.77,0:34:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N好的
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.31,0:34:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, are you about a size 14?\N你大概穿十四号吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.94,0:34:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry?\N什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.06,0:34:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,(GIRL GROANING)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.54,0:34:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,(十四号)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.46,0:34:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,MAN: Good.\N好
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.76,0:34:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,(GIRL WHIMPERING)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.81,0:35:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good. Good.\N哦，好啊，好啊
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.50,0:35:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,MAN: Hold!\N抓着！
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.67,0:35:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,(GRUNTING)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.49,0:35:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,一！
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.85,0:35:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,(WHISTLE BLOWS)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.22,0:35:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Starling!\N斯达琳！
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.18,0:35:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Outside. Let's go.\N出去，我们走吧
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.06,0:35:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Cindy, in the ring for Starling. Let's go!\N辛蒂，进场代替斯达琳。我们走吧！
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.19,0:35:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,(SIRENS BLARING)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.36,0:35:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,FBI! Hold it! Hold it right there!\NFBI！站住！站住不许动！
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.28,0:35:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Saddle up. Pack your field gear. You're moving out.\N打包，收拾你的装备，你要出发了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.08,0:35:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're going with Crawford.\N- Where?\N- 你会跟克劳福德一起去\N- 去哪里？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.58,0:35:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Found a girl's body down in West Virginia.\N在西弗吉尼亚南部发现了一名女子尸体
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.37,0:35:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Been in the water about a week.\N她在水里一周了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.54,0:36:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like a Buffalo Bill-type situation.\N看来是水牛比尔干的
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.25,0:36:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,(AIRPLANE ENGINE WHIRRING)
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.13,0:36:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,(西弗吉尼亚州克莱县)
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.13,0:36:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,(联邦调查局)
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.22,0:36:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,CRAWFORD: He keeps them alive for three days.\N他让她们活了三天
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.89,0:36:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know why.\N我们不知道原因
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.43,0:36:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no evidence of rape or physical abuse prior to death.\N死前没有强奸或虐待的迹象
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.68,0:36:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All the mutilation you see there is postmortem.\N这些伤口都是死后造成的
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.06,0:36:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, three days.\N三天……
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.81,0:36:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he shoots them, skins them, and dumps them.\N然后他开枪射死她们，剥皮和弃尸
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.78,0:36:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Each body in a different river.\N每个尸体弃置在不同的河里
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.65,0:36:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The water leaves us no trace evidence of any kind.\N河水冲走了证据
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.91,0:36:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Fredrica Bimmel, the first one.\N那是第一个，弗瑞德瑞卡·比默尔
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.62,0:36:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Her body was the only one he took the trouble to weight down,\N她的尸体是唯一被他费力沉下去的……
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.70,0:36:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,so actually, she was the third girl found.\N实际上，她是第三个被发现的
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.71,0:36:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,After her, he got lazy.\N继她之后，他变得懒惰了
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.92,0:36:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Let's see.\N好的，我们看看
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.01,0:36:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Circles where the girls were abducted,\N圆圈是那些女子被掳走的位置……
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.09,0:36:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,arrows where their bodies were found.\N箭嘴是尸体被发现的地点
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.43,0:36:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This new one today washed up here.\N今天这个被冲到这里来
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.68,0:36:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Elk River, West Virginia.\N在西弗吉尼亚州埃尔克河被发现
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.83,0:37:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at him, Starling. Tell me what you see.\N斯达琳，仔细看看，告诉我你有什么发现
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.66,0:37:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he's a white male.\N他是个白种男人
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.29,0:37:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Serial killers tend to hunt...\N连环杀手，倾向于……
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.46,0:37:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,within their own ethnic groups.\N在自己的族群中猎杀
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.04,0:37:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not a drifter.\N他不是个流浪者
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.17,0:37:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got his own house somewhere, not an apartment.\N他有自己的独立房子而不是公寓
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.88,0:37:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\N为什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.01,0:37:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What he does with them takes privacy.\N他下毒手时，需要私人地方
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.59,0:37:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in his 30s or 40s.\N他年约三、四十岁
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.68,0:37:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got real physical strength,\N孔武有力……
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.22,0:37:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,combined with an older man's, uh, self-control.\N还有中年人的自制能力
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.14,0:37:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He's cautious, precise.\N谨慎而精确
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.23,0:37:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's never impulsive. He'll never stop.\N他从来不冲动，也不会罢休
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.48,0:37:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?\N为什么不？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.32,0:37:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a real taste for it now.\N他已经迷上了这回事
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.78,0:37:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He's getting better at his work.\N而且越来越熟练
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.49,0:38:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Not bad, Starling.\N不错，斯达琳
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.33,0:38:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Questions?\N有问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.83,0:38:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.\N有的
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.50,0:38:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't mentioned anything...\N你没有提及……
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.37,0:38:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,about the information contained in my report...\N我报告里的任何资料……
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.17,0:38:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or Dr. Lecter's offer, sir.\N或者莱克特医生的提议
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.34,0:38:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm considering it.\N我正在考虑中
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.17,0:38:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you sent me in there, isn't it?\N所以你派我去病院？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.22,0:38:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,To get his help on Buffalo Bill, sir?\N找他协助缉捕水牛比尔？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.43,0:38:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if that was the case, then I just...\N如果那是事实……
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.68,0:38:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wish I was in on it. That's all.\N我希望可以早点知道罢了
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.35,0:38:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had sent you in there with an actual agenda,\N如果以真正目的派你去……
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.69,0:38:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Lecter would have known it instantly.\N莱克特会立刻识破的
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.65,0:38:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He would have toyed with you, then turned to stone.\N他会玩弄你，什么也不会说
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.62,0:38:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,(格瑞格殡仪馆)
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.46,0:38:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,(PEOPLE CHATTERING)
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.73,0:39:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. Sheriff Perkins, these are the FBI people.\N打扰了，珀金斯警长，这些是联邦调查局人员
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.23,0:39:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheriff Perkins. Jack Crawford, FBI.\N珀金斯警长，我是联邦调查局的杰克·克劳福德
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.15,0:39:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Special Agent Terry, Agent Starling.\N这是泰瑞特别探员和斯达琳探员
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.94,0:39:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate being invited to your jurisdiction.\N感谢邀请我们来到你们的管辖区
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.49,0:39:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't call you. That was somebody from the State Attorney's office.\N我没有邀请你们，是州政府检察官办公室的某人找你们的
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.87,0:39:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll extend you every courtesy, but right now...\N我们会全力合作，但现在……
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.08,0:39:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheriff, this type of sex crime has certain aspects.\N警长，这类性罪行有一些特定的细节
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.58,0:39:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd just as soon discuss in private.\N我认为该在私底下谈论
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.00,0:39:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\N你明白吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.01,0:39:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,(ORGAN PLAYING)
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.49,0:41:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- PERKINS: Oscar, fetch Dr. Akin from the chapel.\N- Yes, sir.\N- 奥斯卡，去教堂叫区医生来\N- 是的，长官
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.32,0:41:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,斯达琳，回这边来\NStarling, we're back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.45,0:41:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell Lamar to come on when he's finished playing his music.\N告诉拉玛弹完了风琴之后过来
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.70,0:41:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. We'll be sending in a minute.\N是的，我们稍后会传过来
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.04,0:41:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this working?\N行了？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.29,0:41:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I need a six-way linkup.\N我需要搭建六线联系
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.04,0:41:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Chicago, Detroit...\N芝加哥、底特律……
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.84,0:41:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What? What?\N什么？什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.30,0:41:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,(PEOPLE CHATTERING)
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.43,0:41:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me! Excuse me, gentlemen.\N对不起！对不起，先生们
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.22,0:41:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You officers and gentlemen, listen here now.\N各位警官先生，听我说
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.56,0:41:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There's things we need to do for her.\N我们要替她做一些事情
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.23,0:41:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that you all brought her this far...\N我知道你们把她大老远带来了这里……
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.14,0:41:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and that her folks would thank you if they could...\N她的家人会感谢……
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.90,0:42:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for your kindness and your sensitivity.\N你们的善意和体谅
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.23,0:42:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, please, go on now and let us take care of her.\N现在请离开吧，让我们照顾她好了
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.45,0:42:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on, now.\N走吧
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.91,0:42:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N谢谢你们
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.37,0:42:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,(OFFICER CHATTERING ON POLICE RADIO)
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.96,0:42:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N谢谢
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.96,0:42:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,CRAWFORD: Okay, good.\N很好
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.76,0:42:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right. West Virginia. Elk River.\N是的，西弗吉尼亚埃尔克河
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.55,0:42:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand by for transmission.\N准备传送
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.64,0:42:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,(BEEPING)
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.43,0:42:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ray.\N瑞
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.99,0:42:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,CRAWFORD: Doctor, Lamar, let's take a look at her.\N医生，拉玛，咱们来看看她吧
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.26,0:43:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Jesus.\N天啊
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.35,0:43:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Starling.\N斯达琳，行了
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.98,0:43:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill.\N比尔
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.17,0:43:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Star-shaped contact entrance wound over the, uh, sternum.\N胸骨上有星形的伤口
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.84,0:43:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, muzzle stamp at the top.\N上面有个枪口印记
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.01,0:43:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,DR. AKIN: Wrongful death.\N死于非命
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.39,0:43:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,"Wrongful death."\N“死于非命”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.35,0:43:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll have to go to the state pathologist at Claxton.\N她要被送去克莱克斯顿的病理学家那里
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.77,0:43:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I better get back to that service.\N我还是回那个丧礼去了
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.14,0:44:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Lamar will help you.\N拉玛会帮你们的
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.19,0:44:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Almighty.\N老天爷
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.06,0:44:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,(CAMERA CLICKING)
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.19,0:44:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,CRAWFORD: What else do you see, Starling?\N你还观察到什么，斯达琳？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.32,0:44:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she's not local.\N她不是当地人
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.08,0:44:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Her ears are pierced three times, and there's, uh...\N她穿了三个耳洞，还有……
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.45,0:44:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Glitter nail polish. It looks like town to me.\N闪亮的指甲油，看来是城市人
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.21,0:44:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Two of her fingernails are broken off,\N她有两只指甲断了……
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.01,0:44:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's, uh, there's dirt or grit under them.\N指甲下有泥土和沙粒
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.22,0:44:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like she's tried to ciaw her way through something.\N她好像想爬过一些什么似的
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.89,0:44:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ray, get pictures of her teeth.\N瑞，替她的牙齿拍照
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.35,0:44:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll fax them through Missing Persons.\N稍后传真到失踪人口组
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.77,0:44:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,RAY: Right.\N好的
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.74,0:44:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do another.\N再拍一张
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.16,0:45:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,She's got something in her throat.\N她喉咙里有什么东西
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.17,0:45:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When a body comes out of the water,\N当尸体被捞出水面时……
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.13,0:45:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,lots of times there's, like, leaves and things in the mouth.\N口里总会有些树叶之类的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.45,0:45:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that, some kind of seedpod?\N那是什么？某种豆荚吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.08,0:45:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No, sir. That's a bug cocoon.\N不，是一只虫茧
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.17,0:45:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way that could get way down in there like that.\N它决不可能自己走进去的
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.09,0:45:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Not unless somebody shoved it in there.\N除非有人把它塞进去
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.09,0:45:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll be easier to print when we turn her over.\N我们把她翻过来会较易采指纹
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.72,0:45:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Lamar, will you give me a hand with this?\N拉玛，你能帮我一把吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.22,0:46:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,LAMAR: Yes, sir, I will.\N好的
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.81,0:46:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Jack. What do you make of these?\N哦，杰克，你看这些是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.81,0:46:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Different configuration than the other victims.\N跟其他死者的形状不同，拍几张大特写
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.98,0:46:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Get close-ups.\N拍些近照
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.32,0:46:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Victim's skin removed...\N这次的死者……
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.82,0:46:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,this time in two large diamond-shaped sections above the buttocks.\N臀部以上有两块菱形的皮肤被剥去
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.32,0:46:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Stellate exit wound level with the second or the third thoracic vertebrae...\N伤口底部靠近第二或第三节脊骨……
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.08,0:46:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,approximately six inches from the right shoulder blade.\N上端距离右肩胛骨大约六英寸
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.62,0:46:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,CRAWFORD: Starling?\N斯达琳？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.29,0:46:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When I told that sheriff...\N我对那个警长说……
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.63,0:46:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we shouldn't talk in front of a woman,\N我们不该在女人面前谈……
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.00,0:46:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that really burned you, didn't it?\N那令你很气恼吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.92,0:46:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just smoke, Starling.\N那只是个烟幕，斯达琳
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.42,0:46:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to get rid of him.\N我要打发他走
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.55,0:46:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It matters, Mr. Crawford.\N那很重要，克劳福德先生
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.38,0:46:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Cops look at you to see how to act.\N警察们想看你怎样应付
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.97,0:46:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It matters.\N那很重要
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.56,0:46:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Point taken.\N你明白了
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.85,0:46:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ligature marks found around the wrists,\N手腕周围有被捆绑的痕迹……
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.32,0:46:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,not around the ankles.\N足踝就没有
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.03,0:46:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This would indicate that the skinning was postmortem.\N显示死后才剥皮的
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.40,0:46:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.84,0:47:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,RODEN: Time, Pilch. My move.\N时间到了，轮到我
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.14,0:47:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,PILCHER: No fair. You lured him with produce.\N不公平，你用食物引诱它
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.97,0:47:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Tough noogies. Still my turn.\N真无赖，还是轮到我
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.48,0:47:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice and slow, baby.\N宝贝，慢慢来
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.02,0:47:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If the beetle moves one of your men, does that still count?\N如果那只甲虫推动你的棋子，也算数吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.69,0:47:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course it counts. How do you play?\N当然算数，你怎么玩的？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.07,0:47:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Agent Starling?\N斯达琳探员？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.24,0:47:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,RODEN: Where the heck did this come from?\N这东西从哪里来的？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.24,0:47:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's practically mush.\N它粘糊糊的
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.03,0:47:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It was found behind the soft palate of a murder victim.\N在一个被杀死者身上找到的
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.37,0:47:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The body was in the Elk River, West Virginia.\N尸体在西弗吉尼亚的埃尔克河里
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.71,0:47:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Buffalo Bill, isn't it?\N是水牛比尔干的吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.12,0:47:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid I can't tell you any more about that.\N恐怕我不能透露
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.96,0:47:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,PILCHER: We heard about it on the radio.\N我们在电台听到了
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.29,0:47:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean this is like a clue from a real murder case? Cool!\N这是一起真实谋杀案的线索？酷！
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.71,0:47:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just ignore him. He's not a Ph.D.\N别管他，他又不是博士
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.63,0:48:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A Sphingid. Ceratomia, maybe.\N小角天蛾，可能是
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.85,0:48:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, he's a big sucker.\N它是只大吸血鬼
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.97,0:48:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.43,0:48:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's check morphology.\N咱们查看一下形态学
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.77,0:48:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\N啊哈
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.94,0:48:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you do when you're not detecting, Agent Starling?\N斯达琳探员，你不查案时会做什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.45,0:48:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I try to be a student, Dr. Pilcher.\N做个学生，皮尔切博士
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.41,0:48:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You ever go out for cheeseburgers and beer?\N你会外出吃奶酪汉堡和喝啤酒吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.95,0:48:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The amusing house wine?\N那有趣的招牌酒？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.29,0:48:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you hitting on me, Doctor?\N博士，你是不是对我有意？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.54,0:48:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N是的
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.96,0:48:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,RODEN: Got you.\N找到了！
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.13,0:48:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you got, Roden?\N你找到了什么，罗登？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.25,0:48:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Agent Starling, meet Mr. Acherontia styx.\N斯达琳探员，这个是阴间冥河
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.34,0:48:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Weird.\N真奇怪
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.59,0:48:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Better known to his friends as the Death's Head Moth.\N认识它的人多叫它做骷髅飞蛾
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.89,0:48:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And where does it come from?\N它从哪里来的？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.43,0:48:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what's strange.\N这正是古怪之处
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.68,0:48:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- They only live in Asia.\N- Asia?\N- 它们只活在亚洲\N- 亚洲？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.48,0:48:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In this country, they'd have to be...\N在这个国家，他们得用……
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.69,0:48:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,specially raised from imported eggs.\N进口的虫卵来进行特殊繁殖
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.44,0:48:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody grew this guy, fed him honey and nightshade,\N有人饲养这只东西，喂它吃蜜糖和茄类植物……
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.03,0:48:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,kept him warm.\N给它保暖
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.32,0:49:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody loved him.\N有人很爱它
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.04,0:49:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,(INSECTS BUZZING)
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.55,0:49:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,(MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.85,0:49:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,(CATHERINE MUMBLING)
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.31,0:49:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,CATHERINE: Where are you?\N你在哪里？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.19,0:49:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me out of here!\N放我出去！
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.78,0:49:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,(CATHERINE SCREAMING)
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.95,0:49:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,(HUMMING)
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.72,0:49:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,喂！
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.87,0:49:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,(BARKS)
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.33,0:49:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't leave!\N救我！
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.83,0:49:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk to me, please!\N求你救我
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.54,0:50:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't you answer me? Please!\N干嘛你不答我？求求你！
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.09,0:50:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning. I'm Donna Ferucchi.\N各位早，我是多娜·费鲁奇
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.05,0:50:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Gene Cassel with sports.\N我是报导体育的吉恩·卡塞尔
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.64,0:50:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm Tim Langhorn.\N我是提姆·郎霍
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.14,0:50:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Our top story for this morning.\N今早的头条新闻如下
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.01,0:50:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Catherine Martin,\N凯瑟琳·马丁……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.39,0:50:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the 25-year-old daughter of Senator Ruth Martin,\N鲁思·马丁参议员的25岁女儿……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.18,0:50:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,listed first as a missing person,\N一度被列为失踪人士……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.98,0:50:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is now believed to have been kidnapped...\N相信她已经被称为……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.73,0:50:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,by the serial killer known only as Buffalo Bill.\N『水牛比尔』的连环杀手所绑架
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.57,0:50:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Memphis police sources indicate...\N孟斐斯市警方说……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.90,0:50:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that the missing girl's blouse...\N该名失踪女孩的上衣……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.24,0:50:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,has been identified, sliced up the back...\N已被找到，这件上衣后部被割破……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.28,0:50:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in what has become a kind of grim,\N剪开的地方呈齿牙状……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.16,0:50:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,all-too-familiar calling card.\N这正是『水牛比尔』的标志
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.99,0:50:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Young Catherine Martin, as we've said,\N年轻的凯瑟琳·马丁，众所周知……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.70,0:50:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is the only daughter of U.S. Senator Ruth Martin,\N是田纳西州共和党参议员……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.04,0:50:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the Republican junior senator from Tennessee.\N鲁思·马丁的独生女
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.37,0:50:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And while her kidnapping is not, at this point,\N虽然这起绑架案目前来看……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.29,0:50:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,considered to be politically motivated,\N不具有政治动机……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.04,0:50:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,nevertheless, it has stirred the government to its highest levels.\N但政府最高层仍然相当重视
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.21,0:50:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Reached for a comment on the ski slopes of Stowe, Vermont,\N正在佛蒙特州斯托滑雪的总统……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.22,0:50:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the president himself said to be,\N接受访问时表示……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.34,0:50:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and I quote, "Intensely concerned."\N他『极度关注』
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.26,0:50:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just moments ago, Senator Martin...\N马丁参议员于较早前……
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.80,0:50:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- taped this dramatic personal plea:\N- Excuse me.\N- 录了以下的呼吁……\N- 借过
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.85,0:50:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,MARTIN: I'm speaking now to the person who is holding my daughter.\N我现在对挟持小女的人说话
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.77,0:51:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Catherine is very gentle and kind.\N凯瑟琳是非常温柔和善良的
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.82,0:51:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk to her, and you'll see.\N你跟她谈谈就知道
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.36,0:51:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the power. You are in charge.\N你有力量，你有控制权
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.87,0:51:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you can feel love and compassion.\N我知道你能感受到爱和善心的
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.58,0:51:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a wonderful chance to show the whole world...\N你有一个向全世界展示的大好机会……
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.63,0:51:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can be merciful as well as strong,\N就是你是仁慈而强大的……
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.17,0:51:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're big enough to treat Catherine...\N你有能力善待凯瑟琳……
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.67,0:51:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,better than the world has treated you.\N比这个世界待你更好
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.59,0:51:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You have that power.\N你有那种能力
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.81,0:51:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.\N求你了
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.97,0:51:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter is Catherine.\N我的女儿是凯瑟琳
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.02,0:51:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,ARDELIA: Boy, that's smart.\N天啊，真是聪明
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.10,0:51:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Release her unharmed.\N不加损害释放她
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.31,0:51:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus, that's really smart.\N天啊，真的很聪明
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.85,0:51:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,MAN: She keeps repeating the name.\N她不断重复那个名字
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.15,0:51:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If he sees Catherine as a person and not just an object,\N如果他视凯瑟琳为一个人而非物件……
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.65,0:51:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it's harder to tear her up.\N就难以下毒手
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.95,0:51:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Please. Release my little girl.\N求你放了我的女儿
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.28,0:51:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're doing, Miss Starling,\N斯达琳小姐，你来干什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.70,0:51:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming into my hospital to conduct an interview...\N你第三次来我的医院进行访问……
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.99,0:51:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and refusing to share information with me for the third time.\N并仍然拒绝跟我分享任何信息
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.92,0:52:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, I told you,\N先生，我说过了……
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.25,0:52:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,this is just a routine follow-up on the Raspail case.\N这不过是拉斯佩尔案的例行后续调查
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.50,0:52:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He is my patient. I have rights.\N他是我的病人，我有知情权
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.71,0:52:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that, sir.\N我明白，先生
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.01,0:52:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I am not just some turnkey, Miss Starling.\N听着，斯达琳小姐，我不是个笨蛋
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.43,0:52:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the number for the U.S. Attorney's office.\N这是美国司法部长办公室的电话号码
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.89,0:52:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, either you discuss this with him,\N请你要么跟他谈……
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.23,0:52:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or you let me do my job. Do you understand?\N要么让我执行任务，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.61,0:52:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARICE: If your profile helps us catch Buffalo Bill\N如果你的分析能帮助我们抓到水牛比尔……
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.03,0:52:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in time to save Catherine Martin,\N及时救出凯瑟琳·马丁……
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.28,0:52:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the senator promises you a transfer...\N参议员答应把你转送到……
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.87,0:52:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to the V.A. Hospital at Oneida Park, New York,\NV.A.医院，它位于纽约奥尼达公园……
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.91,0:52:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,with a view of the woods nearby.\N可以看到附近的园林景色
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.33,0:52:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Maximum security still applies, of course.\N当然仍是高度设防的
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.25,0:52:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd have reasonable access to books.\N你可以阅读书籍
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.71,0:52:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Best of all, though.\N最好的是……
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.05,0:52:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,One week of the year,\N每年有一周……
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.72,0:52:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you get to leave the hospital and go here.\N你可以离开医院去这里
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.22,0:52:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Plum Island.\N普拉姆岛
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.06,0:53:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day of that week you may walk on the beach,\N在那里的一星期里，你都可以在沙滩漫步……
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.40,0:53:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you may swim in the ocean for up to one hour,\N也可以在海中畅泳一小时
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.06,0:53:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,under SWAT team surveillance, of course.\N当然是受到特警的监视
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.11,0:53:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And there you have it.\N这些资料给你
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.62,0:53:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A copy of the Buffalo Bill case file.\N水牛比尔的档案副本
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.83,0:53:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A copy of the senator's offer.\N参议员提供的条件副本
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.41,0:53:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This offer is non-negotiable and final.\N这个建议是无谈判余地的
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.42,0:53:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If Catherine Martin dies, you get nothing.\N凯瑟琳·马丁死了你就一无所得
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.34,0:53:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,(THUDDING)
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.35,0:53:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,"Plum Island Animal Disease Research Center."\N“普拉姆岛动物病症研究中心”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.60,0:53:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds charming.\N听来很不错
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.94,0:53:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's only part of the island.\N这只是那个岛的一部分
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.27,0:53:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a very, very nice beach.\N那个岛有非常棒的海滩
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.86,0:53:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Terns nest there. There's beautiful...\N岛上有燕鸥巢，有漂亮的……
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.40,0:53:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Terns? Hmm.\N燕鸥？嗯
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.45,0:54:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If I help you, Clarice, it will be "turns" with us, too.\N如果我帮你，克拉丽丝，这也会是我们的转机
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.66,0:54:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Quid pro quo.\N对等交换
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.79,0:54:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you things, you tell me things.\N我们互相交换资料吧
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.87,0:54:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Not about this case, though. About yourself.\N但不是关于这个案件，是关于你自己
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.88,0:54:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Quid pro quo. Yes or no?\N对等交换，行还是不行？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.26,0:54:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes or no, Clarice?\N行还是不行？克拉丽丝？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.01,0:54:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor little Catherine is waiting.\N可怜的小克拉丽丝在等着呢
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.05,0:54:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Go, Doctor.\N好吧，医生
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.56,0:54:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your worst memory of childhood?\N你最糟的童年记忆是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.14,0:54:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The death of my father.\N家父去世
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.74,0:54:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me about it. And don't lie, or I'll know.\N告诉我，别说谎，不然我会知道的
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.86,0:54:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a town marshal,\N他是镇上的警长……
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.19,0:54:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and one night he surprised two burglars...\N有一晚他意外遇上两个……
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.70,0:54:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of the back of a drugstore.\N从药房走出来的窃匪
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.33,0:54:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They shot him.\N他们向他开枪
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.37,0:54:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Was he killed outright?\N他当场死亡？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.79,0:54:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No. He was very strong.\N不是，他很强壮
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.38,0:54:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He lasted more than a month.\N熬了一个多月
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.17,0:54:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother died when I was very young,\N我母亲在我年幼时去世
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.47,0:54:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so my father had become the whole world to me,\N所以我父亲就成了我的全部世界
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.80,0:55:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and when he left me, I had nothing.\N他去世后，我一无所有
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.39,0:55:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I was ten years old.\N我那时十岁
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.14,0:55:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You're very frank, Clarice.\N你非常坦率，克拉丽丝
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.06,0:55:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it would be quite something to know you in private life.\N我认为了解你的个人生活很有用处
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.86,0:55:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Quid pro quo, Doctor.\N对等交换，医生
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.65,0:55:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So tell me about Miss West Virginia.\N那么告诉我西弗吉尼亚州小姐的情况吧
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.03,0:55:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Was she a large girl?\N她是不是块头很大？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.83,0:55:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N是的
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.04,0:55:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Big through the hips? Roomy?\N大屁股？肉团团？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.66,0:55:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They all were.\N死者们全都是
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.54,0:55:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What else?\N还有什么线索？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.88,0:55:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She had an object deliberately inserted into her throat.\N她的喉咙被异物用心地塞住
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.88,0:55:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that hasn't been made public yet.\N现在这个细节还没有正式公布
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.76,0:55:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know what it means.\N我们还不知道这是什么意思
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.88,0:55:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it a butterfly?\N是一只蝴蝶吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.76,0:55:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. A moth.\N是的，一只飞蛾
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.93,0:55:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the one we found in Benjamin Raspail's head an hour ago.\N一小时前，我们在本杰明·拉斯佩尔的头颅内也找到了
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.56,0:55:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does he place them there, Doctor?\N为什么他把它们放进去，医生？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.61,0:55:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The significance of the moth is change.\N飞蛾的特点是转变
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.74,0:56:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Caterpillar into chrysalis or pupa,\N幼虫变成蝶蛹或者蛹……
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.37,0:56:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and from thence into beauty.\N再变成美丽的蝴蝶
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.33,0:56:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Billy wants to change, too.\N咱们的比尔也想转变
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.91,0:56:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no correlation in literature...\N变性癖和暴力之间……
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.71,0:56:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,between transsexualism and violence.\N是没有严格意义上的关联的
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.42,0:56:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Transsexuals are very passive...\N变性癖者是很被动的……
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.09,0:56:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Clever girl.\N很聪明
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.75,0:56:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so close to the way you're gonna catch him.\N你已经很接近抓到他了
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.71,0:56:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you realize that?\N知道吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.42,0:56:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Tell me why.\N不知道，为什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.09,0:56:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,After your father's murder, you were orphaned.\N你父亲被杀后你成了孤儿
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.30,0:56:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened next?\N后来怎么样了？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.68,0:56:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't imagine the answer is on those second-rate shoes, Clarice.\N我相信答案并非在那双廉价鞋子上，克拉丽丝
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.56,0:56:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to live with my mother's cousin and her husband in Montana.\N我去了蒙大拿州，跟我母亲的表妹夫妇同住
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.23,0:56:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They had a ranch.\N他们有一个牧场
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.19,0:56:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it a cattle ranch?\N牧牛场？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.95,0:56:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheep and horses.\N牧羊和马
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.16,0:56:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How long did you live there?\N你在那里住了多久？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.62,0:56:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Two months.\N两个月
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.04,0:56:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Why so briefly?\N为什么这么短？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.75,0:56:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I ran away.\N我跑掉了
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.29,0:56:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, Clarice?\N为什么？克拉丽丝
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.02,0:56:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Did the rancher make you perform fellatio?\N牧场主人有没有逼你口交？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.46,0:56:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he sodomize you?\N他有没有鸡奸你？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.13,0:57:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No. He was a very decent man.\N没有，他是个很正派的人
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.93,0:57:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Quid pro quo, Doctor.\N对等交换，医生
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.85,0:57:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Billy is not a real transsexual.\N比尔不是个真正的变性癖者
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.43,0:57:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But he thinks he is. He tries to be.\N但他以为自己是，他试图做到
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.68,0:57:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He's tried to be a lot of things, I expect.\N我相信他试图做很多事情
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.81,0:57:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And you said that I was very close...\N你说过我已经很接近……
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.15,0:57:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to the way we would catch him.\N抓到他了
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.36,0:57:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you mean, Doctor?\N你什么意思，医生？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.82,0:57:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There are three major centers for transsexual surgery.\N有三间主要做变性手术的中心
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.49,0:57:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Johns Hopkins, the University of Minnesota, and Columbus Medical Center.\N约翰霍普金斯、明尼苏达州大学和哥伦布医疗中心
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.03,0:57:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be surprised if Billy had applied for sex reassignment...\N如果比尔曾经向它们或其中一家申请做变性手术……
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.41,0:57:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,at one or all of them and been rejected.\N而遭到拒绝，我也不会感到惊讶
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.46,0:57:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,On what basis would they reject him?\N他们根据什么来拒绝他？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.17,0:57:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,LECTER: Look for severe childhood disturbances...\N试图寻找同暴力有关的……
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.96,0:57:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,associated with violence.\N童年创伤吧
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.05,0:57:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Billy wasn't born a criminal, Clarice.\N比尔并非天生是个罪犯，克拉丽丝
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.13,0:57:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He was made one through years of systematic abuse.\N他是多年来系统性的虐待导致的
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.26,0:57:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Billy hates his own identity, you see,\N比尔讨厌自己的身份……
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.02,0:57:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and he thinks that makes him a transsexual.\N他以为那是令他成为变性癖者的原因
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.85,0:57:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But his pathology is a thousand times more savage...\N但他的病征要更凶残……
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.86,0:57:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and more terrifying.\N和可怕千倍
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.36,0:58:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It rubs the lotion on its skin.\N它涂润肤液在身上
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.36,0:58:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It does this whenever it's told.\N它听到指示总会依着做
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.20,0:58:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Mister, my family will pay cash.\N先生，我的家人会付钱的
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.20,0:58:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever ransom you're asking for, they'll pay it.\N无论你要多少赎金，他们都会付
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.00,0:58:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It rubs the lotion on its skin,\N它涂润肤液在身上……
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.29,0:58:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,or else it gets the hose again.\N否则又要挨打了
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.67,0:58:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she will, Precious. She will get the hose.\N是的，她会的，珍宝，她会挨打的
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.13,0:58:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,(SOBBING) Okay, okay, okay.\N好吧，好吧，好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.72,0:58:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. I'm there.\N我做吧
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.89,0:58:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N好的
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.56,0:58:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mister, if you let me go,\N先生，如果你放我走……
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.81,0:58:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't... I won't press charges.\N我不会……我不会起诉你
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.56,0:58:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise.\N我保证
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.94,0:58:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,See, my mom is a real important woman.\N我妈是个重要人物
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.53,0:58:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess you already know that.\N相信你也知道吧
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.82,0:58:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it places the lotion in the basket.\N它把润肤液放在篮里
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.20,0:58:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Please! Please! I want to go home.\N求求你！求求你！我想回家
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.58,0:58:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go home, please! Please, I want to...\N我想回家！求求你！放我吧
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.46,0:58:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It places the lotion in the basket.\N把润肤液放在篮里
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.67,0:59:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to see my mommy! Please.\N我想见我妈妈，求你放我吧
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.34,0:59:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to see my mother again.\N我想再见到我妈妈
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.88,0:59:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to... I want to see my mommy.\N我想……我想见我妈妈
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.76,0:59:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Put the fucking lotion in the basket!\N把那他妈的润肤液放在篮里！
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.35,0:59:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,(PRECIOUS BARKING)
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.77,0:59:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,(CATHERINE SCREAMING)
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.37,0:59:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,(SHOUTING)
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.13,0:59:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You still think you're gonna walk...\N你还以为可以在沙滩上……
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.43,0:59:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,on some beach and see the birdies?\N漫步和看鸟儿吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.26,0:59:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,(LAUGHING) No, I don't think so.\N不，我不这样认为
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.10,0:59:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I called Senator Ruth Martin.\N我给凯瑟琳·马丁参议员打过电话
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.73,1:00:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She never heard of any deal with you.\N她没听过任何同你有关的协议
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.15,1:00:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They scammed you, Hannibal.\N他们骗你，汉尼拔
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.23,1:00:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand outside...\N出去……
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.99,1:00:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and shut the door.\N把门关上
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.95,1:00:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Barney.\N巴尼
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.33,1:00:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There never was a deal with Senator Martin, but there is now.\N从没有跟马丁参议员的协议，但现在有了
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.96,1:00:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I designed it.\N是我议定的
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.38,1:00:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I worked in a few conditions for my own benefit as well.\N当然，我也为自己的利益定下了一些条件
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.21,1:00:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Identify Buffalo Bill by name...\N说出水牛比尔的名字……
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.59,1:00:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and if the girl is found in time,\N如果那个女孩及时被发现……
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.51,1:00:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Senator Martin will have you transferred...\N马丁参议员会把你转送到……
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.43,1:00:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to Brushy Mountain State Prison in Tennessee.\N田纳西州的丛树山州立监狱
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.10,1:00:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Answer me, Hannibal.\N回答我，汉尼拔
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.02,1:00:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You answer me now,\N你现在回答我……
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.77,1:00:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or by God, you'll never leave this cell.\N否则，天啊，你休想离开这个牢房
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.61,1:00:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is Buffalo Bill?\N水牛比尔是谁？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.70,1:00:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,His first name is Louis.\N他的名字是路易斯
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.28,1:00:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell the rest to the Senator herself, but only in Tennessee,\N其余的我只会在田纳西州亲自对参议员说……
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.87,1:01:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have a few conditions of my own.\N并且我也有几个条件
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.21,1:01:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Clean him up and get him ready to go.\N替他梳洗一下，准备出发
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.32,1:01:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,DIRECTOR ON PHONE: Jack, Hannibal Lecter is being transferred to Memphis.\N杰克，汉尼拔·莱克特正被转送往孟斐斯途中
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.80,1:01:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Transferred?\N转送？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.22,1:01:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you have a trainee make some sort of...\N你是不是有个见习生……
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.18,1:01:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,phony offer to Lecter in the Senator's name?\N冒参议员之名向莱克特提出一个虚假的建议？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.93,1:01:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I rolled the dice. I had to.\N是的，这是我的主意，我逼不得已
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.93,1:01:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she's mad as hell, Jack.\N她气疯了，杰克
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.27,1:01:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul Krendler's over here from Justice.\N司法部的保罗·克伦德勒来了
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.35,1:01:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She's asking him to take over in Memphis.\N她要求他在孟斐斯接手
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.44,1:01:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,(SIRENS WAILING)
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.59,1:01:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,(孟斐斯市国际机场)
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.84,1:01:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Memphis, Dr. Lecter.\N莱克特医生，欢迎来到孟斐斯
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.67,1:01:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Lieutenant Boyle.\N我是波依尔警长
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.13,1:01:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Sergeant Patrick.\N这位是帕特里克警官
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.55,1:01:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we're gonna treat you as good as you treat us.\N我们会像你待我们一样好的
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.76,1:02:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You be a gentleman, you gonna get three hots and a cot.\N你做个绅士，就会得到舒服的待遇
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.06,1:02:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir. If you sign right here,\N先生，请在这里签名……
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.73,1:02:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll have us a legal transfer.\N我们完成法律移交
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.61,1:02:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is it?\N在哪签？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.28,1:02:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, sir. Use mine.\N这个，先生，用我的吧
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.78,1:02:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,(BREATHING HEAVILY)
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.16,1:03:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Senator Martin, Dr. Hannibal Lecter.\N马丁参议员，汉尼拔·莱克特医生
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.33,1:03:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Lecter,\N莱克特医生……
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.38,1:03:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought an affidavit guaranteeing your new rights.\N我带了一份宣誓书保证你新的权利
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.17,1:03:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll want to read it before I sign.\N在我签署前你会想先看看
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.22,1:03:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't waste your time or Catherine's time...\N我不会为了小利益……
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.31,1:03:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,bargaining for petty privileges.\N而耽误你或凯瑟琳的时间
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.68,1:03:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Clarice Starling and that awful Jack Crawford...\N克拉丽丝·斯达琳和杰克·克劳福德……
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.85,1:03:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,have wasted far too much time already.\N已经浪费了太多时间
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.06,1:03:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I only pray they haven't doomed the poor girl.\N但愿他们没有害死那个可怜的女孩
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.19,1:03:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me help you now and I will trust you when it is all over.\N让我帮你吧，事成后我会信任你
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.03,1:03:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You have my word. Paul?\N我答应你，保罗
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.49,1:03:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Buffalo Bill's real name is Louis Friend.\N水牛比尔的真名是路易斯·弗伦德
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.37,1:03:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I met him just once.\N我只见过他一次
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.71,1:03:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He was referred to me in April or May, 1980,\N1980年4、5月间由我的病人……
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.71,1:03:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,by my patient Benjamin Raspail.\N本杰明·拉斯佩尔转介给我的
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.63,1:03:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They were lovers, you see.\N他们是爱人
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.84,1:03:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But Raspail had become very frightened.\N但拉斯佩尔变得很害怕
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.05,1:04:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, Louis had murdered a transient...\N显然，路易斯谋杀了一个过往旅客……
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.72,1:04:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and done things with her skin.\N并用他的皮肤做了一些东西
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.85,1:04:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We need his address and a physical description.\N我们要他的地址和容貌特征
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.02,1:04:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, Senator.\N告诉我，参议员……
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.23,1:04:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you nurse Catherine yourself?\N你有没有亲自哺育凯瑟琳？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.86,1:04:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\N什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.93,1:04:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you breast-feed her?\N你有没有给她喂奶？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.61,1:04:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, wait a minute!\N等一下！
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.91,1:04:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I did.\N是的，我是的
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.70,1:04:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Toughened your nipples, didn't it?\N令你的乳头变得坚挺，是吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.58,1:04:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You son of a bitch!\N你这个狗娘养的！
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.45,1:04:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Amputate a man's leg, and he can still feel it tickling.\N一个人的腿被切除了，他还能感到痒
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.42,1:04:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, Mom, when your little girl is on the slab,\N告诉我，妈妈，当你的小女儿被杀时……
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.00,1:04:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,where will it tickle you?\N你哪里会感到痒？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.09,1:04:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this thing back to Baltimore.\N把这个畜生带回巴尔的摩
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.59,1:04:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Five-foot-ten, strongly built, about 180 pounds.\N五英尺十英寸，身材魁悟，约一百八十磅
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.76,1:04:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hair, blond. Eyes, pale blue.\N金发、浅蓝色眼睛
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.56,1:04:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd be about 35 now.\N他现在大约三十五岁
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.93,1:04:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he lived in Philadelphia, but may have lied.\N他声称住在费城，但可能是说谎
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.06,1:04:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I can remember, Mom.\N我只记得这么多了，妈
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.10,1:04:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I think of any more, I will let you know.\N如果我再想起什么，我会通知你的
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.28,1:05:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and, Senator, just one more thing.\N哦，还有，参议员，还有一件事
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.07,1:05:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Love your suit.\N你的套装很漂亮
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.70,1:05:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.87,1:05:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,CHILTON: I tell you now that in a meeting earlier this evening...\N我现在告诉你，在今晚较早前……
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.12,1:05:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with Senator Ruth Martin,\N与鲁思·马丁参议员会面时……
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.46,1:05:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Lecter agreed to assist in the investigation...\N莱克特医生同意协助调查……
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.58,1:05:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of trying to find the abductor...\N帮助追拿凯瑟琳·马丁的……
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.51,1:05:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,(谢尔比县法院大楼)
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.04,1:05:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of Catherine Martin, Buffalo Bill.\N绑架者，水牛比尔
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.46,1:05:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you fit in, sir?\N你是怎么促成的，先生？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.59,1:05:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's only through my own unique insight...\N通过我对莱克特医生思想的……
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.17,1:05:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,into Lecter's mind that this breakthrough was possible.\N独特视角，这次突破才成为可能
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.30,1:05:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And Buffalo Bill's real name...\N水牛比尔叫什么名字？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.47,1:05:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Buffalo Bill's real name is now a matter of record...\N水牛比尔的名字是目前有关……
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.22,1:05:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with the proper authorities.\N当局的秘密
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.43,1:05:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- Can you give us any more information?\N- My name is Dr. Frederick Chilton.\N- 能不能再多给我们些信息？\N- 我是弗德里克·奇尔顿医生
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.10,1:05:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- How do you spell that?\N- C-H...\N- 怎么拼的？\N- 奇特的奇……
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.35,1:05:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you with Dr. Chilton's group?\N你是和奇尔顿医生一起的吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.52,1:05:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, I just saw him outside, sir.\N我刚在外面见到他
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.15,1:05:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Access to Lecter is strictly limited.\N接近莱克特是受到严格限制的
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.98,1:05:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been getting death threats.\N我们接到死亡恐吓
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.65,1:05:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand, sir.\N我明白的
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.45,1:05:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Log in. Check your weapon.\N登记和把武器放下
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.25,1:05:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,KRENDLER: Well, I can't take all the credit for myself.\N我不能把功劳归到我一人身上
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.79,1:05:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Senator Martin, the Justice Department, the people at the FBI,\N马丁参议员、司法部和联邦调查局的……
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.42,1:05:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the folks at the Baltimore State Hospital.\N巴尔的摩州立医院的人员
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.67,1:06:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And now for the hard part, apprehending the suspect.\N最困难就是逮捕那个疑匪
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.26,1:06:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, folks, I'm gonna have to catch a flight.\N对不起，我要赶飞机了
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.22,1:06:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,(PHONE RINGING)
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.72,1:06:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Command desk. Officer Jacobs.\N指挥台，我是杰科布斯警察
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.60,1:06:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,(路易斯·弗伦德飞禽、猥亵)
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.31,1:06:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,(铁)
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.65,1:06:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,OFFICER: Is it true what they're saying?\N他们说的是事实吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.94,1:06:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\N什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.70,1:06:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He's some kind of vampire?\N他是个吸血殭尸？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.07,1:06:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't have a name for what he is.\N他们没有替他取名
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.87,1:06:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.54,1:06:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You do know the rules, ma'am?\N小姐，你知道规矩的吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.79,1:06:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Lieutenant Boyle. I've questioned him before.\N知道，我以前问过他问题
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.75,1:06:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.\N去吧
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.04,1:07:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening, Clarice.\N克拉丽丝，晚安
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.50,1:07:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you might like your drawings back, Doctor.\N我想你可能想要回你的画吧
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.09,1:07:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Just until you get your view.\N直到你有自己的景观
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.76,1:07:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How very thoughtful.\N真是周到
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.89,1:07:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Or did Jack Crawford send you for one last wheedle\N还是在你们破案前，杰克·克劳福德派你来……
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.06,1:07:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,before you're both booted off the case?\N说最后一次的花言巧语？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.69,1:07:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I came because I wanted to.\N不，是我自己想来的
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.61,1:07:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,People will say we're in love.\N人家会说我们在恋爱呢
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.03,1:07:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,(CLICKING TONGUE)
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.20,1:07:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Anthrax Island.\N安斯拉克斯岛
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.87,1:07:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That was an especially nice touch, Clarice.\N确实很动人，克拉丽丝
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.12,1:07:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours?\N你想的？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.71,1:08:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N是的
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.21,1:08:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! That was good.\N对！很好
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.18,1:08:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.30,1:08:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Pity about poor Catherine, though.\N但我同情可怜的凯瑟琳
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.26,1:08:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Tick-tock, tick-tock, tick-tock, tick-tock.\N滴答，滴答，滴答，滴答
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.80,1:08:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Your anagrams are showing, Doctor.\N你的字谜有破绽了
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.18,1:08:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Louis Friend?\N路易斯·弗伦德？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.56,1:08:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Iron sulfide, also known as Fool's Gold.\N是硫化铁，也叫做黄铜铁
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.89,1:08:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Clarice.\N克拉丽丝
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.98,1:08:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Your problem is you need to get more fun out of life.\N你的毛病是，你要活得轻松一点
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.40,1:08:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You were telling me the truth back in Baltimore, sir.\N你在巴尔的摩时说了真话，先生
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.44,1:08:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Please continue now.\N现在继续吧
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.53,1:08:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I have read the case files, have you?\N我看过那些档案了，你看过吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.49,1:08:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything you need to find him...\N你要缉拿他的资料……
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.82,1:08:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is right there in those pages.\N都在里面
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.66,1:08:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Then tell me how.\N那么教我怎样做
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.83,1:08:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,First principles, Clarice. Simplicity.\N首要的原则，克拉丽丝，是简易
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.91,1:08:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.71,1:08:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Read Marcus Aurelius.\N读读马可·奥勒留的《沉思录》吧
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.29,1:08:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Of each particular thing, ask what is it in itself?\N凡事都问：它的内在是什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.92,1:08:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What is its nature?\N它的本质是什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.13,1:08:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What does he do, this man you seek?\N你寻找的这个人，他做什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.51,1:08:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He kills women.\N杀害女人
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.10,1:08:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No! That is incidental.\N不！那是附带发生的
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.81,1:08:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the first and principal thing he does?\N他第一和首要的是做什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.68,1:09:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What needs does he serve by killing?\N他杀人是为了满足什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.56,1:09:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger.\N愤怒
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.81,1:09:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, social acceptance...\N嗯，社会认同……
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.47,1:09:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.69,1:09:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and, uh, sexual frustrations...\N还有……呃……和性困惑……
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.86,1:09:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No! He covets.\N不是！他贪婪
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.28,1:09:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.16,1:09:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That is his nature.\N那是他的本性
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.29,1:09:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do we begin to covet, Clarice?\N我们怎样才会开始贪婪，克拉丽丝？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.46,1:09:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we seek out things to covet?\N我们是否去寻找贪婪的东西？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.50,1:09:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Make an effort to answer now.\N尝试回答吧
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.63,1:09:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No. We just...\N不是，我们只是……
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.34,1:09:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No. We begin by coveting what we see every day.\N我们看见日常的东西就开始贪婪
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.88,1:09:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you feel eyes moving over your body, Clarice?\N你有没有感到一些眼睛在盯着你，克拉丽丝？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.93,1:09:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't your eyes seek out the things you want?\N你的眼睛，又可有寻找你要的东西？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.06,1:09:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Yes. Now please tell me how.\N有的，请你告诉我吧
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.85,1:09:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It is your turn to tell me, Clarice.\N不，轮到你告诉我了，克拉丽丝
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.78,1:09:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.90,1:09:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have any more vacations to sell.\N你再没有假期可哄骗我了
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.07,1:09:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you leave that ranch?\N为什么你离开那个牧场？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.90,1:09:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, we don't have any more time for any of this now.\N我们没有时间再玩这一套了
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.99,1:09:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But we don't reckon time the same way, do we, Clarice?\N但我们的时间观念是不同的，不是吗，克拉丽丝？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.74,1:10:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all the time you'll ever have.\N你只有这么多的时间
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.75,1:10:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Later. Now, please, listen to me. We've only got five...\N稍后吧，请听着，我们只有五个……
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.25,1:10:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No! I will listen now.\N不！我现在就要听！
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.84,1:10:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,After your father's murder, you were orphaned.\N父亲被杀后，你就成了孤儿
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.76,1:10:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You were ten years old.\N你当时才十岁
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.09,1:10:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You went to live with cousins on a sheep and horse ranch in Montana.\N你去了蒙大拿，跟一些养羊马的表亲同住
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.93,1:10:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And?\N之后呢？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.18,1:10:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And one morning, I just ran away.\N我在一个早上跑掉了
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.14,1:10:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Not "just", Clarice. What set you off?\N不是的，什么驱使你离开？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.90,1:10:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You started at what time?\N你在什么时候出发？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.15,1:10:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Early. Still dark.\N很早，天还没亮
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.69,1:10:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then something woke you, didn't it?\N有东西吵醒你，是吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.24,1:10:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it a dream? What was it?\N是不是一个梦？是什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.29,1:10:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.07,1:10:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard a strange noise.\N我听到一种奇怪的声音
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.08,1:10:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it?\N是什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.99,1:10:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It was screaming.\N是尖叫声
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.34,1:10:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.62,1:10:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Some kind of screaming, like a child's voice.\N像小孩的尖叫声
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.79,1:10:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you do?\N你怎么做？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.92,1:10:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I went downstairs, outside.\N我下楼，走出屋外
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.21,1:10:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.30,1:11:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I crept up into the barn.\N我偷进了壳仓
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.97,1:11:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so scared to look inside, but I had to.\N我很害怕看进去，但又必须看
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.18,1:11:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And what did you see, Clarice?\N你看见了什么？克拉丽丝？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.14,1:11:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you see?\N你看见了什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.11,1:11:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Lambs. They were screaming.\N一些羔羊，它们在尖叫
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.43,1:11:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.86,1:11:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They were slaughtering the spring lambs?\N他们在宰杀那些羔羊？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.95,1:11:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And they were screaming.\N而它们在尖叫
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.28,1:11:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And you ran away?\N那你就跑掉了？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.04,1:11:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\N不是
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.87,1:11:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,First I tried to free them. I...\N最初我想释放它们。我……
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.54,1:11:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I opened the gate to their pen, but they wouldn't run.\N我打开它们的闸门，但它们不跑
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.08,1:11:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They just stood there, confused.\N它们只是站在那里，很困惑的
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.38,1:11:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't run.\N不肯走
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.80,1:11:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But you could and you did, didn't you?\N但你可以走，你也走了，是不是？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.17,1:11:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I took one lamb, and I ran away as fast as I could.\N是的，我抱起一只羊就拔足逃跑
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.72,1:11:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Where were you going, Clarice?\N你当时要去哪里，克拉丽丝？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.10,1:11:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\N我不知道
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.66,1:11:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.39,1:11:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have any food, any water,\N我没有食物和水……
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.31,1:11:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was very cold, very cold.\N而且当时很冷，非常冷
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.86,1:11:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought...\N我以为……
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.98,1:11:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought if I could save just one, but,\N我以为，至少可救下一只羊
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.40,1:11:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,he was so heavy.\N但它很重
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.16,1:12:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He was so heavy.\N真的很重
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.91,1:12:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't get more than a few miles...\N我走不了几哩路……
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.83,1:12:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when the sheriff's car picked me up.\N警长的车就把我截住
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.05,1:12:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The rancher was so angry,\N牧场主人很生气……
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.38,1:12:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,he sent me to live at the Lutheran orphanage in Bozeman.\N把我送到博兹曼的路德会孤儿院
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.97,1:12:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I never saw the ranch again.\N我再没看过那个牧场了
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.89,1:12:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What became of your lamb, Clarice?\N你的羊又怎么样？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.43,1:12:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They killed him.\N他们把它杀了
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.14,1:12:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You still wake up sometimes, don't you?\N有时你仍会惊醒，是吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.60,1:12:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Wake up in the dark and hear the screaming of the lambs?\N在黑暗中醒来，听到那些羔羊的尖叫声？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.91,1:12:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.23,1:12:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N是的
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.07,1:12:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And you think if you save poor Catherine,\N你相信如果把凯瑟琳救了出来……
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.86,1:12:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you could make them stop, don't you?\N可以令它们停止尖叫，是吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.53,1:12:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You think if Catherine lives,\N你相信如果凯瑟琳活着……
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.91,1:12:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't wake up in the dark ever again...\N你就不会在黑夜中……
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.16,1:12:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to that awful screaming of the lambs.\N再被那些可怕的羊叫声惊醒了
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.29,1:12:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I don't know.\N我不知道，我不知道
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.27,1:12:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.34,1:13:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Clarice. Thank you.\N谢谢你，克拉丽丝，谢谢你
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.91,1:13:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.93,1:13:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me his name, Doctor.\N告诉我他的名字
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.85,1:13:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Chilton, I presume.\N是奇尔顿医生吧
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.73,1:13:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you know each other.\N我相信你们是认识的
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.44,1:13:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N好吧
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.53,1:13:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We found her.\N我们找到他了
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.78,1:13:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!\N我们走吧！
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.99,1:13:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your turn, Doctor.\N医生，轮到你了
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.95,1:13:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Out.\N出去
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.12,1:13:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me his name.\N说出他的名字
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.24,1:13:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, ma'am, I've got orders.\N抱歉，我接到命令
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.54,1:13:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to put you on a plane.\N要把你送上飞机
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.00,1:13:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on now.\N走吧
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.46,1:13:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Brave Clarice.\N勇敢的克拉丽丝
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.67,1:13:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You will let me know when those lambs stop screaming, won't you?\N那些羔羊停止尖叫时，你会告诉我的，是吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.55,1:13:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me his name, Doctor!\N告诉我他的名字，医生！
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.63,1:13:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Clarice!\N克拉丽丝！
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.22,1:13:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Your case file.\N你的档案
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.65,1:13:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!\N喂！
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.97,1:13:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Clarice.\N再见，克拉丽丝
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.26,1:14:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,(PEOPLE CHATTERING)
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.89,1:14:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,(CLASSICAL PIANO MUSIC PLAYING ON RECORDER)
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.32,1:14:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.67,1:14:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready when you are, Doc.\N医生，准备好就来吧
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.92,1:15:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Just another minute, please.\N请等一会
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.80,1:15:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The son of a bitch demanded a second dinner.\N那个混蛋竟然还要再吃一顿晚饭
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.31,1:15:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Lamb chops, extra rare.\N还要极生的羊排
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.39,1:15:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonder what he wants for breakfast.\N不知道他早餐要吃什么
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.85,1:15:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Some damn thing from the zoo?\N动物园里的怪物？
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.98,1:15:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,(PEMBRY CHUCKLING)
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.22,1:15:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,(化学喷雾)
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.50,1:15:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening, gentlemen.\N两位，晚安
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.38,1:15:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Doc. Grab some floor.\N好的，医生，蹲下吧
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.59,1:15:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Same drill as before, please.\N跟以前的程序一样
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.01,1:15:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.47,1:15:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready when you are, Sergeant Pembry.\N彭布瑞探员，准备好了
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.24,1:16:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,PEMBRY: Okay.\N行了
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.12,1:16:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,BOYLE: Hand me that, would you?\N递给我吧
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.46,1:16:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.\N谢谢
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.47,1:16:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,LECTER: Mind the drawings, please.\N请小心那些画
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.64,1:16:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N谢谢你
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.33,1:17:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Jimmy, watch it! He's got me!\N彭布瑞，小心！他把我扣住了！
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.30,1:17:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,(SCREAMING)
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.64,1:17:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ!\N天啊
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.80,1:17:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,(GROANING)
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.11,1:17:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,(SCREAMING)
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.84,1:17:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,(PIANO MUSIC RESUMES)
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.73,1:18:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,(PEMBRY GRUNTING)
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.76,1:18:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready when you are, Sergeant Pembry.\N彭布瑞探员，准备好就来吧
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.81,1:18:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,(PEOPLE CHATTERING)
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.60,1:18:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,TATE: What is this shit?\N究竟什么回事？
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.06,1:18:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Did somebody go up on five?\N有人上了五楼？
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.98,1:18:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Nobody went up.\N不，没有人上去过
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.99,1:18:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Call Pembry. Ask him...\N叫彭布瑞，问他……
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.28,1:18:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,(GUN FIRING)
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.66,1:19:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,CP, shots fired on five. Repeat.\N指挥部，五楼有枪声，重复
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.78,1:19:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Shots fired on five.\N五楼有枪声
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.04,1:19:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sergeant Tate.\N泰特警官
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.95,1:19:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,(OFFICER CHATTERING ON RADIO)\N去，五楼有枪声
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.08,1:19:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,TATE: Holy shit.\N天啊！
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.46,1:19:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- What the hell?\N- Bitch!\N- 怎么了？\N- 混蛋！
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.84,1:19:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up.\N闭嘴！
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.38,1:19:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Bobby, get the vest.\N鲍比，拿防弹衣来
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.71,1:19:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Sarge.\N是，警官
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.30,1:19:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,TATE: Brady, Howard, cover...\N布拉迪、霍华德，掩护……
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.68,1:19:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Look!\N看！
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.60,1:19:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It stopped.\N它停了
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.47,1:19:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Seal off a 10 block radius.\N封锁方圆十幢楼的范围
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.27,1:19:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Get me the SWAT team and an ambulance double-quick.\N召特警队和救护车来，快点！
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.14,1:19:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going up.\N我们上楼去
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.10,1:19:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,(OFFICER CHATTERING ON RADIO)
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.51,1:19:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,TATE: Pembry?!\N彭布瑞？！
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.59,1:20:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Boyle?!\N波依尔？！
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.98,1:20:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God!\N天啊！
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.49,1:20:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Go.\N去
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.33,1:20:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- Clear!\N- OFFICER: Clear!\N- 没有人\N- 没有人
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.88,1:20:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Command post, two officers down.\N指挥站，两个警察死了
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.73,1:20:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.84,1:20:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,OFFICER 1 : Clear!\N没有人！
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.92,1:20:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,OFFICER 2: Clear!\N没有人！
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.47,1:20:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Lecter's gone, Sarge.\N警官，莱克特不见了
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.88,1:20:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The prisoner is missing.\N囚犯失踪了
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.80,1:20:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Boyle's gun is gone, Sergeant.\N波依尔的配枪不见了
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.81,1:20:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Repeat. Lecter is missing and armed.\N重复，莱克特持械失踪了
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.47,1:20:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He stripped the bed.\N他拿走了床铺
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.06,1:20:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Might be making a rope.\N可能用来做绳
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.60,1:20:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Check all windows.\N搜查所有窗户
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.35,1:20:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Where the fuck is my ambulance?\N该死的救护车在哪里？
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.40,1:20:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He's alive.\N他还活着
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.48,1:20:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sergeant Tate, he's alive!\N泰特警官，他仍活着！
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.90,1:21:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Get ahold of him where you can feel his hands, son.\N扶着他，抚摸他的手，孩子
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.91,1:21:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk to him.\N跟他说话
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.74,1:21:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I say?\N说什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.03,1:21:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Jim Pembry! Now talk to him, damn it!\N他是吉姆·彭布瑞！跟他说话，该死！
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.83,1:21:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Lecter is missing and armed.\N莱克特持械失踪了
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.37,1:21:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Pembry. Pembry, can you hear me?\N彭布瑞……你听得到我吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.46,1:21:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He took Boyle's gun.\N他拿走了波依尔的配枪
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.04,1:21:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Pembry got off one round.\N彭布瑞开过一枪
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.55,1:21:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a chance Lecter was hit.\N莱克特可能中了枪的
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.59,1:21:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep breathing in and out. That's it.\N继续呼吸吧，就这样
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.80,1:21:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doing a good job.\N你做得很好
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.47,1:21:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You look real good there.\N你看上去很好
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.80,1:21:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you look... You look real good.\N对，你看上去……你看上去真的很好
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.18,1:21:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,(SIRENS WAILING)
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.77,1:21:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- You ready?\N- Let's go!\N- 你准备好了吗？\N- 咱们上！
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.12,1:21:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it.\N咱们行动吧
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.20,1:21:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.\N咱们上
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.12,1:21:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.09,1:22:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking good, Pembry. You're gonna make it.\N很好，彭布瑞，你支持得住的
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.34,1:22:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just fine. You're doing all right. That's right.\N你没事的，你很好
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.51,1:22:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I need that IV now.\N我要作静脉注射
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.80,1:22:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Lactated ringers.\N乳酸盐液
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.01,1:22:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we get the strap?\N我们能不能拿那条带子来？
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.35,1:22:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the fucking oxygen?\N见鬼的氧气在哪里？
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.47,1:22:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- Looking good, buddy. That's right.\N- TATE: Bob!\N- 老兄，情况很好，很好\N- 鲍勃！
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.27,1:22:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay with me. Stay with me here.\N留下来陪我，留下来陪我
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.77,1:22:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We're losing him. Downstairs. Take him!\N他不行了，去楼下，快点！
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.81,1:22:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And up!\N抬起！
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.57,1:22:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Elevator! Out of the way!\N电梯！让开！
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.78,1:22:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the way!\N让开！
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.12,1:22:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,OFFICER ON RADIO: CP to Tate.\N指挥部呼叫泰特
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.16,1:22:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger, Lieutenant. Tate here.\N收到，我是泰特
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.16,1:22:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,(BEEPING)
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.20,1:22:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm on the elevator bringing Pembry down.\N我现在乘电梯送彭布瑞下来
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.17,1:22:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He seems to be hanging on.\N他看来支持得住
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.83,1:22:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Top three floors secured.\N最高的三层楼封锁了
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.50,1:22:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Main stairwell secured.\N主要楼梯封锁了
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.47,1:22:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We think he's on two.\N我们相信他在二楼
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.56,1:23:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Tate, are you still with me?\N泰特，你还能听到吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.69,1:23:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We're pretty sure he's somewhere on two, sir.\N我们相当肯定他在二楼，长官
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.15,1:23:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all for now. Over.\N这是目前全部情况。完毕
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.03,1:23:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.59,1:23:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He's on the roof of the elevator.\N他在电梯顶
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.81,1:23:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, guys.\N好的，大家来
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.78,1:23:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I see him.\N我看到他了
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.20,1:23:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a gun by his hand. He's not moving.\N他的手边有一支枪，他没有动
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.45,1:23:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,One warning. We need him alive.\N警告，我们要生擒他
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.41,1:23:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,JOHNNY: Got him.\N知道
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.33,1:23:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Lecter?\N莱克特？
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.96,1:24:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Put your hands on your head.\N把双手放在头上
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.25,1:24:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,One in the leg.\N向腿射一枪
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.38,1:24:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,(GUN CLICKING)
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.77,1:24:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No movement.\N没有动静
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.52,1:24:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Johnny, hold your fire. We're coming into the car.\N约翰，不要开枪，我们要进入电梯
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.69,1:24:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We're opening the hatch.\N我们会打开盖口
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.82,1:24:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch his hands.\N小心他的手
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.28,1:24:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's any fire, it'll come from us. Affirm.\N如果有开火，会是我们开的，确定
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.45,1:24:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,JOHNNY: Got it.\N明白
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.80,1:24:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,(SIREN WAILING)
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.64,1:24:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Memphis General, this is Medical Unit 26.\N孟斐斯医院，这是26号车
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.81,1:25:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We're inbound with a 50-year-old male police officer...\N我们会送来一名五十岁男性警官……
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.48,1:25:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,with severe facial lacerations. Weapon unknown.\N他面部有严重割伤，伤害武器不明
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.98,1:25:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got grand mal seizure activity, but he's postictal now.\N他全身出现抽搐，情况严重
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.03,1:25:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,WOMAN: Copy that.\N收到
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.15,1:25:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Vital signs are good.\N重要器官情况良好
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.65,1:25:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Pressure is 1 30 over 90.\N血压是130/90
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.15,1:25:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- 90?\N- Yeah, that's right. 90.\N- 血压90？\N- 对，是90，
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.70,1:25:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Pulse, 84.\N脉搏84
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.07,1:25:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got him on lactated ringers running.\N我们给他注射了乳酸盐液
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.83,1:25:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And the patient is on 1 0 liters...\N病人正在吸十公升的氧气
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.71,1:25:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,小心！
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.34,1:25:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,ARDELIA: They found the ambulance...\N他们在孟斐斯机场……
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.59,1:25:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in a parking garage at Memphis Airport.\N一个车库里发现了那辆救护车
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.92,1:25:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The crew was dead.\N工作人员死了
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.51,1:25:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He killed a tourist, too.\N他还杀了一名游客
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.34,1:25:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Got his clothes, cash.\N拿了他的衣服和钞票
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.64,1:25:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,By now he could be anywhere.\N他现在可能在任何地方
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.56,1:25:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't come after me.\N他不会来对付我的
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.68,1:25:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?\N哦，真的？
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.72,1:25:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, he won't. I can't explain it.\N不，他不会的，我无法解释
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.30,1:25:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.27,1:25:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He... He would consider that rude.\N他……认为那样做很无礼
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.27,1:25:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.11,1:25:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over. She's dead.\N都完了，她死定了
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.19,1:25:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not your fault it worked out like this.\N事情演变至此不是你的错
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.19,1:25:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is that, Lecter said everything we need to catch him with...\N问题是，莱克特说我们需要捉拿他的资料……
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.57,1:25:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is right here in these pages, only I can't...\N都在这里，只是我无法……
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.70,1:25:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Lecter said a lot of things.\N莱克特医生说了很多事
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.24,1:25:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He's here, Ardelia.\N阿德利亚，他在这里的
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.52,1:26:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,(SNIFFING)
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.23,1:26:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this Lecter's handwriting?\N这是莱克特的笔迹吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.07,1:26:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,"Clarice, doesn't this random scattering of sites...\N“克拉丽丝，这样杂乱地分布现场……
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.82,1:26:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,"seem desperately random?\N“看上去不是有点极度随意吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.82,1:26:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"Like the elaboration of a bad liar.\N“像个差劲的说谎者的精心策划
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.08,1:26:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,"Ta, Hannibal Lecter."\N“汉尼拔·莱克特”
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.79,1:26:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Desperately random? What does he mean?\N『极度随意』？他是什么意思？
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.58,1:26:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Not random at all maybe.\N可能根本不是随意
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.12,1:26:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Like there's some pattern here.\N是有一个模式的
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.13,1:26:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but there is no pattern,\N对，但并没有模式……
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.59,1:26:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or the computers would have nailed it.\N否则电脑也会发现的
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.46,1:26:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They're even found in random order.\N尸体甚至是不依次序被发现的
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.92,1:26:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Random because of the one girl.\N不依次序是因为那个女孩
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.13,1:26:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The one he weighted down.\N那个被他沉下的女孩
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.97,1:27:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- Fredrica Bimmel...\N- Right.\N- 弗瑞德瑞卡·比默……\N- 对
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.10,1:27:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.22,1:27:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,From Belvedere, Ohio.\N来自俄亥俄州的贝尔维迪尔
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.98,1:27:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,First girl taken, third body found. Why?\N第一个遇害的女孩，尸体是第三个被发现，为什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.77,1:27:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she didn't drift. He weighted her down.\N她没有漂浮，他把她沉下去
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.15,1:27:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What did Lecter say about the first principles?\N莱克特说的首要原则是什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.61,1:27:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Simplicity.\N简易
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.40,1:27:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What does this guy do? He covets.\N这个家伙做什么？他贪婪
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.87,1:27:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we first start to covet?\N我们怎样开始贪婪的？
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.79,1:27:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We covet what we see...\N我们贪婪见到的东西……
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.54,1:27:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day.\N每天见到的
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.08,1:27:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hot damn, Clarice.\N该死，克拉丽丝
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.79,1:27:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew her.\N他认识她的
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.98,1:27:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,(俄亥俄州贝尔维迪尔市)
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.38,1:28:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,(BIRDS TWITTERING)
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.59,1:28:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,(SQUEAKING)
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.49,1:28:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bimmel?\N比默尔先生？
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.00,1:28:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's me.\N我是
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.71,1:28:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello. I'm Clarice Starling. I'm with the FBI.\N你好，我是克拉丽丝·斯达琳，联邦调查局探员
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.92,1:28:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARICE: I sure appreciate you letting me...\N比默尔先生，如果你能让我……
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.46,1:28:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,take a look around, Mr. Bimmel.\N四周看看，我会很感激你的
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.97,1:29:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know nothing new to tell you.\N我没有什么新资料给你了
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.30,1:29:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Police been back here so many times already.\N警方已经来过很多次
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.89,1:29:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Fredrica went into Chicago on the bus to see about a job.\N弗瑞德瑞卡坐巴士去芝加哥求职
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.23,1:29:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She left the interview okay.\N她好端端地离开面试
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.23,1:29:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,She never come home.\N再也没有回家
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.57,1:29:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Her bedroom's how she left it.\N她的卧房是原封不动的
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.11,1:29:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Upstairs. Door to the left.\N在楼上，左边那一间
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.59,1:29:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.68,1:30:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,(MUSIC BOX PLAYING)
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.64,1:31:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,(CAT MEOWING)
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.49,1:32:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARICE: He's making himself a woman suit, Mr. Crawford,\N他在替自己做女装，克劳福德先生……
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.78,1:32:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,out of real women.\N用真的女人做
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.95,1:32:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And he can sew, this guy. He's very skilled.\N他还懂得缝纫，他很熟练
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.26,1:32:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.74,1:32:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a tailor or a dressmaker or...\N他是个裁缝或……
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.41,1:32:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,CRAWFORD: Starling!\N斯达琳！
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.54,1:32:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they're all so big. He has to keep them alive...\N所以她们都身材肥大，他让她们活着……
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.43,1:32:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.71,1:32:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so he can starve them a while,\N逼使她们挨饿……
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.87,1:32:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so he can loosen their skin and take...\N令她们的皮肤松弛，然后……
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.96,1:32:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Starling.\N斯达琳
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.50,1:32:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.04,1:32:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Starling! Starling, we know who he is and where he is!\N斯达琳！斯达琳，我们知道了他的身份和下落！
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.59,1:32:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're on our way right now.\N我们快到达了
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.92,1:32:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,CLARICE: Where?\N哪里？
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.09,1:32:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Calumet City, edge of Chicago.\N芝加哥卡柳梅特城
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.30,1:32:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Be on the ground in 45 minutes with HRT.\N我45分钟后会和特警队降落
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.89,1:32:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's great news, sir, but how...\N哦，这是好消息，长官，但怎么……
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.39,1:32:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Johns Hopkins came up with some names.\N约翰霍普金斯提供了一些名字
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.43,1:32:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We fed him into "Known Offenders."\N我们输入已知犯人的档案
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.06,1:32:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Subject's name is Jamie Gumb, AKA John Grant.\N他叫杰米·冈姆布，又名约翰·格兰特
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.31,1:32:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Lecter's description is accurate. He just lied about the name.\N莱克特的描述是正确的，他只是捏造了那个名字
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.98,1:32:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to this. Customs had some paper on him.\N听我说，海关有些关于他的资料
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.06,1:32:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.39,1:32:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.57,1:32:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They stopped a carton two years ago at LAX.\N两年前他们在洛杉矶机场查到一个纸箱
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.74,1:32:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Live caterpillars from Surinam.\N是一些来自苏里南的活毛虫
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.12,1:32:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The addressee was a Jame Gumb.\N收件人叫詹姆·冈姆布
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.62,1:32:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Chicago's only 400 miles from here.\N芝加哥离这里只有四百哩
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.29,1:32:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be there in...\N我很快就到那里……
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.41,1:33:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no, Starling.\N不，不，不，斯达琳
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.54,1:33:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not enough time.\N没有时间了
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.67,1:33:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We want him for murder, not kidnapping.\N我们要控告他谋杀，不是绑架
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.00,1:33:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you to link him to the Bimmel girl before he's indicted.\N在起诉他前，要找出他与弗瑞德瑞卡·比默的关系
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.50,1:33:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,See what you can dredge up in Belvedere.\N你去贝尔维迪尔看有什么发现
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.34,1:33:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir. You bet. I'll do my best.\N是的，长官，我会尽力的
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.68,1:33:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Starling, we wouldn't have found him without you.\N斯达琳，没有你我们就找不到他，
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.68,1:33:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.51,1:33:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's gonna forget that. Least of all me.\N大家都会记着这点，尤其是我
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.59,1:33:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.39,1:33:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir.\N谢谢，长官
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.81,1:33:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Mr. Crawford.\N谢谢你，克劳福德先生
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.31,1:33:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Crawford?\N克劳福德先生？
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.33,1:33:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,CATHERINE: Thanks for the scraps, asshole.\N混蛋，谢谢那些冷饭菜汁
